Item_Response: Archeologists have a very important job. They find artifacts from way back in history when George Washington was alive and artifacts from Jamestown Island. They used many tools to keep the artifacts safe and in great condition. In this report you will learn what the archeologists found and used to give you history we learn today!!!       In 1994, a group of people were interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archeologists Project.The project was designed to discover the secrets of the James Fort in Virginia. For over 200 years, people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river. Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around.       The first objects were found in 1861. They found uncovered armor and weapons. They also discovered the floors of buildings. The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area. That's when they finally found James Fort!       The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground. The marks showed where the fort's walls used to be. The archeologists also found eleven cellars and ten buildings all within the border of the fort. Today, the group finds nearly one million objects each year!       Archeologists used a lot of tools. Most of them were used to clean off dirt off the artifacts. They used picks, shovels, whisks, dustpans, knifes, wheelbarrows, skim shovels, and trowels.       I hope you learned a lot about archeologists and someday you will be one too!!!

Item_Response: The Importance of Archeology                                                    by Kelsey Miller          Have you ever wondered what life would be like if we knew nothing about our history?  Without archeology we wouldn't know anything about our past. In 'Finding Fort James,' and 'Digging up George Washington's Past,' archeologists teach us about the history of Fort James, and about George Washington as a boy. Not only does it teach us about our history, but it's interesting!          In 'Finding Fort James,' archeologists are searching for Fort James to find out if it really was washed out by a river. In there journey they find out where the fort was and they also find out a lot about how people's daily lives went, and how people survived. Without archeology we would know nothing about this.          In 'Digging up George Washington's Past,' archeologists are trying to find out more about George Washington's life as a boy. They believe that the stone base of George's house is still there. They use a high tech computer to track what is underground.                     Technology also helps archeologists find out about the past. People use analyzers and metal detectors to find things and figure out what things are.Thank goodness for technology.            As you can see the job of an archeologist is very important. without archeology there would be lots of trouble with finding out things like the problems  people had in the past and how do we prevent them.          In conclusion, without archeology we would know nothing about our past...Or anyone's past.

Item_Response: The archeologists have a tough job to do.  With hard work and tough digging  they have to find artifacts or bones.  This is the life of an archeologist.         As an archeologist one main event was to dig up the artifacts in Fort James.  It was tough because they had to dig something up that was 200 years ago.  It was dug up in ruins by a flooding river.  Fort James was built in 1607, that's 406 years ago!  Since archeology was started way back then they have found the first artifacts in 1861!  They found armor and weapons in the ruins.  The National Park Service led a five-year study of it to figure out how they used the land.  That's when they finally found where Fort James was built!  Finally they found about how the people of Fort James did their daily routine.  The dicovery of Fort James was very exciting to archeology life.         The second and last discovery was digging Goerge Washington's past.  As you know Washington was the fist president of the United States.  I will not tell you about Goerge Washinton, but about digging up his past.  They had a numerous amount of teams with 35 people on each team.  The first team scans the area using 3D computers.  When the information got back to them they got to work.  They digged for their lives!  Each team got a part (layer) of the dig.  One team got a skim shovel and digged the first layer.  Then it went on to troweling.  Troweling used small shovels, paint brushes, and toothpicks!  It can take up to two weeks of digging a 25-square foot area!  The last team studied the artifacts they found.  A place called Ferry Farm is based on Washington's past.  It has classes, games, and crafts.         This paragraph is based on the tools that the archeologists used.  The pick and shovel are for hard mining.  The whisk and dustpan is to clean the dust from artifacts or make it easier to see the floor.  The knife is used for detailed digging and scraping dirt from the artifacts.   The wheelbarrow is used to move heavy items from one place to another.  The skim shovel is used to carefully remove a thin layer of dirt.  Last, but not least, the trowel is used to scrape and view different layers of soil.         As an areologist it is very hard and takes patience but in the end it is all worth it.

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is to find artifacts that are underground. To do this they must be very careful not to miss anything because that could ruin the whole exhibition. They use many tools to make sure they don't miss anything. Some of the tools they use are pick axes and shovels these tools are used to break up the dirt and get down deep into the ground closer to the artifacts. Also they use whisks and dustpans these tools are used to sweep dirt off artifacts and to clear dirt away from the sight. Other tools are knifes and wheelbarrows the knife is used to get dirt from around the artifacts and the wheelbarrow is used to get dirt away form the sight. The last 2 tools they use are a skim shovel and a trowel, skim shovels are used to remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop and the trowel is used to scrape and cut to view different layer of soil.

Item_Response: archeologists                                             Archeologists are people that dig holes and find artifacts from the past to learn about life back then.They need tools to do it they use shovels,picks,whisks,duspans,wheelbarrows,skim shovels,trowels, and a knife.     We are now going to learn about finding Fort James.        In 1994, a group of people interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Redicovery Archaeological Project.The project was designed to discover the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. for over 200 years,people thought it had been washed away by the river. Some dicoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around.      The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from england to start a new life. Most belived that James Fort was built near the river. It was easier to dock ships there, so it made sense that the settlers would choose that spot. However, objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away. The new spot problably gave the settlers more protection from enemy ships.           the first objects were found in 1861 those items were armor and weapons.They also discovered the floors of buildings.Over 100 years later,a group effort to find the exact spot the fort was built began.           The national park service led a five year study of the area to figure out how the land was used. They knew this would help them decide where to look for proof of the fort. The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area.        That's when they finally found James Fort! The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground.The marks showed where the forts walls used to be. Between all the stories they heard and read,and drawings they made,the archeologists knew it would be shaped like a triangle.They made maps and found out that the fort streched all the way to the river.Then they realized there were stone ledges built over the river. The ledges were designed to hold cannons. The archeologists also found eleven cellars, dozens of burial sites,and ten buildings within the border of the fort.

Item_Response: Have you ever wanted to find dinosaur bones, ancient drawings, and even hidden treasures?! If you have, becoming and archeologist would be a suitable job for you. Archeologists are people who earn money by finding buried treasures and bones! Not only be would you be rich, but you would also be famous and well known by many people.            If you want to become an archeologist, you have to know all the equipment and tools archeologists use. First, you have to know what a pick and shovel is. A pick and shovel are tools used to dig dirt and break stone. Second, a whisk and dustpan are tools used to brush away dust from the excavation site. Third, a knife is used for carefully scraping off the dust from the ancient artifacts. Fourth, a skim shovel has a flat edge for removing layers of soil. Finally, a trowel has a pointy edge and a small handle used for cutting to view the different layers of soil. If you know all these tools you are ready for the next step.            You have to know all the teams to become an archeologist. The first team maps the areas using 3D computers that can track and record what is underground. This information is valuable because the people can know what it looks like before they start digging. Another team focuses on the actual digging. Finally, the last team studies the objects that were found for days.            If you think this job suits you, study to become and archeologist. As you can see, archeologist work very hard to find ancient artifacts. Even though becoming and archeologist needs a lot of effort, it is worth it.

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist           An Archeologist is a person who works to find objects that belonged to a person who lived long ago. There are many different teams who do different jobs for this process. The first team finds the place they will be digging at. The next group focuses on the digging itself. The last group studies the results.                 The first team finds the place where the diggers will be digging. That is probably the most important job of them all because if the first group chose a place in the middle of nowhere, where there is nothing to be found, the hunt will not work. They also need something to look for. If they don't know what to look for and don't have information about it, the hunt won't work either. So, they find the place where they will hunt and map it out in detail on a 3D computer. Then, they record the information so that the diggers know what the place looked like before the digging began. That is the first groups job.                  The second team is the digger team. They have a very important job too, because they are the ones do the actual digging. They use very special tools that are great for delicately digging through the earth. They must be very careful in digging, because if they dig too hard, they could destroy the artifacts or even miss them. The most common tool used by the archeologists is the Trowel. Archeologists use it to look at the different layers of soil. Some more tools archeologists use are the pick and the shovel. They are both used to dig through the earth and look closely at the dirt. Once the diggers find what they think is an artifact, they give it to the third team.                  The third team receives the artifact that the diggers find and look very closely at it. They have special tools for that as well. They examine the artifact, determine who it belonged to, and got most of the credit. The diggers got a lot of the credit too, though. This is what the third team does.                       So this is what archeologists do. They have three different teams that work together to find artifacts that belonged to people long ago. All the teams must work extremely hard to get the job done. If I were to be an archeologist, I would want to be in the third team because you get to examine the artifacts the second team finds. I wouldn't want to be in the second team because you have to dig for a long time and give a lot of your effort into it. This is what archeologists do.

Item_Response: An archaeologists job is to find or discover things. They discover objects, artifacts, dinosaurs, sharks and more. They discover things by digging it up. Some archaeologists send out some type of radio length that senses what's underground and knows whats underground. Other archaeologists job is to dig, dig, dig.                       They find things by looking to see if they can spot some sort of clue that there was something there. If they find a mark, they dig in that area to see if there are any objects that tell them that something was there. They also look in the environment or surroundings suggesting that something was there. Then, they use their tools and dig.                       Archeologists use wheelbarrow, picks and shovels, dustpans, whisks, knives, skim shovels and trowels. They use the wheelbarrows for hauling away dirt or artifacts they find. Picks and shovels are used to dig. Whisks and dustpans are used to carefully brush off the artifacts or clear dirt away from the digging site. Knives are used to scrape dirt away from the object. Skim shovels can remove a layer of dirt with each scoop. The trowel is used to scrape and cut the different layers of soil.

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist       Archeologists are scientists that study items from long ago. They dig up objects that can range from dinosaur bones to a gold miner's pipe. Some other examples of what they dig up are items found from old forts. One such fort is Fort James. It is a fort from 1607 where they find close to a million artifacts per year.       The process of finding these artifacts is long and hard. It involves lots of digging and working. First, the archeologists cut away at the Earth with a tool called a skim shovel, which works slowly, removing very small layers of dirt one at a time. They also begin sometimes with picks and bigger shovels. Once the objects are found, it is an equally hard process to study them.       Once artifacts are found in the dirt, a team of people examines them. If the artifacts are dirty, they are brushed off with a tool called a whisk. Then the objects are identified. They are sent off to museums and looked at by many people. They will be admired for the history that they hold and people of all kinds will enjoy them.

Item_Response: Digging up Geore Washington's Past                      Most of  what we know about George Washington comes from his time as a soldier and president . Biographies don't have very much information about his childhood . That's changing , however . Recent discoveries at Washington's childhood home have helped historians know more about Washington as a boy .                How did archeologists find all of these things that were in Washington's house all those years ago ? The process of digging at the Ferry Farm is a careful one . Each year , many teams will work on the site . There can be up to 35 people on a team ! The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what's in the ground. The information is recorded so that people will know what it looks like before people started digging. Another team focuses on the actual digging and the place the team does the digging is called a dig . Those  archeologists start their dig with what are called skim shovels .           The shovels are small ,flat, and sharp that they can remove thin layers of soil is then placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom .This lets the dirt fall out and the artifacts stay in.The diggers also use a process called troweling .Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels,paint brushes ,and wooden picks to remove dirt .It can take up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section ! Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found . The whole process is slow and tiresome , but it is worth it .           No one knew exactly where the Washington house was located since the actual building was long gone .However, archeologists believed that the base under the house was still there .They started digging in 2003.It took over a year , but they finally found it . The first  buildings they found were the kitchen, slve quarters, and storage houses .           The discovery of Washington's house is important for many reasons . First , it gives the citizens of the United States a better understanding of who George Washington before he was famous . We also began to know why he made the decisions he did . Another thing it does is help historians learn about the type of  life Colonial Americans lived . All of these things are key parts of our past as Americans .

Item_Response: Being An Archeologist           Being a archeologist is a hard job. You have to have a lot of skills to be a skilled worker like archeologists. You can't just go out in a historical site and start digging. You need to do research and look at maps to know where to dig. You need to have three skills if you want to be a good archeologist; Perseverance, teamwork, and knowledge. if you have those skills you can become a good archeologist.             Perseverance is a major skill in archeology. The National Park Service led a five year study about Jamestown's Fort James. It took perseverance for archeologists to research Fort James. Imagine yourself studying one topic for five years! It really took a lot of time! And perseverance! So an archeologist's job is important and takes a lot of perseverance.           Teamwork is also a big skill for an archeologist. Without teamwork you can't get anything done. And with an archeologist you need to have teamwork to find artifacts and ancient remains. Without teamwork you can't find artifacts fast and you can't find them easy. You will not even find an artifact if you don't have teamwork. Thats why teamwork is a good skill you need to have if you want to be an archeologist. In the five year study it also took a lot of teamwork. People had to cooperate and work together to find Fort James.           The last skill you need is called knowledge. If you don't have knowledge you can't get artifacts. In 2003 when archeologists believed that a stone base under George Washingtons childhood house it took knowledge to know that it could be under there. They ended up finding many rooms. But it took over a year! You really do need to have knowledge in being an archeologist.           These examples show and prove that you need perseverance, teamwork, and knowledge to be an archeologist. If you decide to be an archeologist you should consider having these skills. It will help you through life and being an archeologist. An archeologists job is mainly to discover artifacts and treasures from the past. An archeologists job is really unique and special.

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is long and tiring. The first thing you have to do is find the spot where you think the debris field is. Next you map it out on  a 3D mapping machine that tells you whats underground. Afterwards you start using shovels and the wheelbarrows to haul out dirt. Next you use a skim shovel to carefully remove thin layers of dirt.       Afterword you would use a Whisk and Dustpan to brush dirt off the artifacts. After that you would then use a small shovel called a trowel it is probably the most common tool in archeology. The trowel does lots of things to help and archeologist one of them is to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil. Another one is that you can maneuver around the artifact and get in the crevices. Finally the last one is that you can use the trowel to smooth out the area where you dug the artifacts up.       My conclusion is that an archeologist's job is very hard and long. Proof that their job is very hard and long is that you have to use so many different tools. And the smaller the tools get the longer it takes to cover as much ground. As  with a big tool you can cover twice as much ground in twice as much time. Finally you can tell that it is a long and hard job is that there are almost 25 people on each dig at one time.

Item_Response: Being an archeologist is very tough work. You must be very careful and very smart. Here are some examples. First you must be very smart by finding out where ancient might be and you must be able to research and things on the computer.       Also you must be smart by digging in the right places so you don't destroy any fragile artifacts. Archeologists have to be so careful that it can take months just to dig up a couple of artifacts. Archeologists have many to special tools for finding lost artifacts. Like many different types of machines, hammers, and drills.       There are many different teams of archeologists there are the research where you use the computer and find things,digging group who dig up the artifacts, and the displayers who clean the things and show them in museums or special places.       Archeologists search from dinosaur fossils to kids toys in the past. An Archeologists main job is to collect stuff to help us understand the far back past. A very old toy were rattles because back then they were pretty easy to make. You could use an animal bone for the whole rattle then place a stone inside the opening of the bone. Normally very young children enjoyed rattles.       Digging up dinosaur bones is probably the hardest and trickiest thing to dig up. The reason is because the bones are thousands of years old and are packed way into the earth. There are over a hundred types of dinosaurs to dig up. That does not mean it is easy to find them though. The computer archeologists team has to find and predict where dinosaurs would have been. Then they send the digging team to the spot and tell its cordinates.       Now the digging team has to get a very special machine that digs deep into the earth. Now the team takes all the dirt they dug up and puts it through a thing that takes all the sand off and leaves the rocks and artifacts there. They search it to try to find fossils or items. When they find a dinosaur fossil they search to find the whole body. If they do they send it to the museum people and they clean the fossil up and put it together.       Soon it is put in a museum. Being an archeologist is a very long prosess. But it is a very good job to have when you are older. It is a really good paying and interesting job and you can have a really fun future being one.

Item_Response: Archeologists               Archeologists are people who dig up artifacts and sometimes even learn more about the history in that particular time period or place. This all may sound simple, but it's not! Archeologists must be very patient and careful with the artifacts and the digging, because if you are not careful with an artifact than you may drop or break it! Also, like I said before, you must be very patient because digging sometimes can take a very long time! Now, you must be thinking, what's so great about artifacts anyways? Well, artifacts are not just a piece of history, they can also tell us more about the history in that time period. Actually, I had already said that earlier, but that is okay.               Now we shall be talking about how artifacts help understand and tell us more about the history. For example in Source #2 it talks about George Washington's history and how some artifacts helped to understand a little bit more about his life, I mean they found clay pipes, and George Washington smoked clay pipes!That is also how archeologists knew that they had found the right house because it was evidence that it was the correct house. Wow! How cool is that! Archeologists can find the place that they are looking for just by having the right facts and finding artifacts! I'm pretty sure that is something that archeologists are trained to do.          Now you must be wondering, ' How do archeologists find and dig up these artifacts, and what do they normally use?', well, hold your horses, because now I about to tell you! Actual archeologists do not just find these artifacts by themselves. No way that would happen! Then finding the artifact or artifacts would take forever! No, that actually doesn't happen, because archeologists work together as a team to discover the artifacts. As a matter of fact, some teams can have up to thirty-five people on the team! No joke! But what do archeologists USE to find these items? You must be wondering. Well right now I shall list a couple of tools that archeologists and their team use to dig up these items. Pick and shovel are used to start most digs to dig near the artifacts. Whisk and dustpan are used to brush dirt off the artifacts, and to clear dirt away from the excavation site, too. The knife is used for careful digging and also to scrape dirt from around the artifacts. The wheelbarrow is used not only to move items from one place to another, also to sometimes to carry dirt away from the excavation site to someplace elsewhere. The skim shovel is used to remove thin layers of soil, carefully, with a flat edge made for that specific purpose. Now I will be telling you about the last tool that is commonly used by archeologists, and it is called the trowel. The trowel is actually probably the most commonly used tool in archeology. It is normally used to cut and scrape to view the different layers of soil, there. Well, there is one more thing used for digging up artifacts in archeology, some teams use 3-D computers that can track what is inside what is in the ground right before the digging, so that you will not have to dig in a place where there isn't anything that you were looking for.Well, now I believe that I have covered all the tools!         Wow! Now I hope that you have at least learned something new about archeology, and archeologists, if you have, good for you! And if you haven't, well, too bad then! Anyways, I still hoped that you have enjoyed my report on archeology, and archeologists! Bye!

Item_Response: An Archeologists Life                                            The job of an archeologist requires patience and time because sometimes, it can take up to 2-4 weeks to finish finding what you're looking for. Archeologists also need to be observant and aware of their surroundings. Something could be laying beneath the dirt 25 feet away from you and you may not notice, so always be aware. You may not think so, but archeologists are very important people. You would be surprised of how much knowledge in history has come from archeologists finding and putting together the puzzles of the past. Archeologists also help people understand famous people from long ago, such as George Washington. Archeologists went out looking for items and hints of his past so people could understand what his life was like before he was even famous.             One of the tools an archeologist uses to find items and hints of the past is a 3D computer that can detect things underneath the surface of the earth. This tool is used in many cases, for it is very important. This device is important to archeologists because it can see more than the human eye can. As I said earlier, something could be laying 24 feet away from you covered in dirt and you may not notice. That's why archeologists use the 3D computer. Although not everything archeologists use is a high-tech device. Archeologists still have to use their own senses to find an item. And archeologists still have to use shovels to dig things up. So archeologists also requires strength.             Some self-operated tools that archeologists still have to use are trowels, skin shovels, wheelbarrows, whisks and dustpans, picks, and shovels. You may have notices that I said shovel twice, but the two shovels I said are two different types of shovels. The skin shovel is used to start the digging. The sharp, flat blade of the shovels helps to remove tough layers of soil that can't be removed by a regular shovel. The wheel barrow is used to put dirt in so other archeologists can take the dirt somewhere else and dump it out, then they bring it back to the whole the other archeologists are digging, then the cycle of that repeats.             Many of the people that may be reading this may feel different about archeologists and may understand them better. I hope that the readers of this report are now truly fascinated by the life of an archeologist.

The project was designed to discover the secrets of the James fort in Jamestown, Virginia. for over 200 years, people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river. some people thought that some discovers might still be around.            The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came England to start a new life. Most believed that James fort was built near the river. did you know that it was easier to dock ships there, so it made sense that the settlers would choose that spot. some people found objects nearby and suggested that the fort was located further away.the new spot mostly gave the settlers more protection from the enemy ships around them.                 Did you know that the first objects were found in 1861. Over 100 years later, a group effort to find to find the exact spot where the fort was built began. The national park service led a five year study of the area to figure out how the land was used. they new it would help them decide where to find the proof of the fort. the first thing they found was a marking on the ground. Did you know that the people that were studying use computer mapping software to make an image of the area.                     Today, the group finds nearly 1 million objects each year. The objects include pottery, tools, coins, and even metal toys for children. While digging in the area, the archaeologists found the trash the settlers threw away, including the bones of animals they ate. they said  that this trash the settlers threw away helped them under stand the way the people in Jamestown lived and what they ate.

Item_Response: Digging for History        Do you know who digs up old artifacts and discovers more about our history? Well, you guessed it! Archeologists. Archeologist have a very important job to do. They dig up things that are still unknown about and they find out more about our marvelous history. Though the job is very tiring and slow, it is all worth it.       First, you'll need some tools! Archeologists have to have many tools to dig things up. Some of the tools they use are the pick and shovel, whisk and dustpan, the knife, the wheelbarrow, and the skim shovel. These help a lot in finding old artifacts. Most of the time, you will need a pick and shovel. They are basically used to dig. The whisk and dustpan are used to brush off dirt from the artifacts but without destroying the artifacts. The knife is for scraping off dirt around the artifact and the wheel barrow is for moving items from one place to another. Lastly, the skim shovel is different from a regular shovel, It has a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.       Next, archeologists need to have accurate measurements to see where the artifacts are. Archeologists use 3D computers that can track what is underground. There are many teams that help out. One team can be up to 35 people! Each team has it's own job, for example, one team can do the actual digging and the other can study the items that were dug up. They can spend days on one artifact which may seem very long; it actually is but it's all worth it in the end.       Then, after the artifacts are dug up, a team studies the artifact that was brought in. And this can help people understand better about our history. When you put the pieces together, you can see how our history connects in one piece. That shows that archeologists have a big job.       In conclusion, archeologist have a very important job to do and that is to find out more about our past and history. They do the hard and tiring work to discover more about history. So that shows that they should be respected. Archeologists have a interesting job and I think it would be fun to have a job like that.

Item_Response: Diggers were  finding artifacts and info about George Washington. Archeologists use  a pick and shovel to dig into the earth close to artifacts. They also use a wisk,dustpan,knife,wheelbarrow,skilm,shovel, and trowel.  They go in teams and 35 people can go on a team. The first team maps an area by using 3 demention computers to trackt what is underground. The other team goes on a dig. Those archeologists start their dig with a skilm shovel.   When archeologists use small shovels,paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt is called Troweling.           Archeologists started digging to find Washington's house in 2003. Records show that the Washington's   house had a fire in it. The diggers found pieces of burt pottery that showed a fire was there. They also foun part of a clay pipe so we know that Washington smoked clay pipes.            Finding Fort James   In 1994, a group of people intrested in studing the past started the jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. The project was desined for discovering the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown,Virginia. For more  than 200 years, people thought a river washed the fort away.        The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life. Most of the people believed that James Fort was built near the river so it was easier to dock ships there so it made sence.  Objects nearby suggested the fort was located far away so the new spot maybe gave the settelers more protection from enemies.       The first objects were found in 1861. Archeologists are the name for scientists that study objects from the past that uncovered armor and wepons. They also dicovered the floors of buildings. Over 100 years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort wwas built began.           The National Park service led a five - year study of the area to figure out how the land was used. They knew that this would help them decide where to look for proof of the fort. The people doing this study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area.       That's when they finally found James Fort! The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground. The marks showed where the fort's walls used to be. Between all the stories they heard and read and the drawlings they made, the archeologists knew that the fort would be shaped like a triangle. They made maps and found out that the fort stretched all the way to the river. Then they realized ther were stone ledges built over the river. The ledges where desined to hold canons. The archeologists also found eleven cellars, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings all within the border of the fort.           Today, the group  finds nearly 1 million objects a year. The objects include pottery,tools, coins, and even metal toys for children. In the 1600s, people used to throw their trash down an unused well or in a pit. While digging in the area, diggers find the trash and animal bones settelers threw away.   The information learned from these objects helps them understand how the people in James Fort lived. Now we know how settelers fought the Powhatan tribe that often attacked them. We also know what the settelers did to survive the difficult years when they had little food.

Well, now you will. Archeologists are scientists who study objects, known as artifacts, from the past. I used 3 resources with facts about archeologists to find the right information. The articles are titled, 'Finding Fort James', 'Digging up George Washingtons Past', and ' Tools Used by Archeologists'.                     In 1994, archeologists found Fort James. The fort was believed, for 200 years, that it was washed away by a river or moving water. The fort was built in 1607 and the first objects giving facts about the past were found in 1861. The artifacts found wwere armor, weapons, and floors of buildings. About 100 years later a team of archeologists worked very hard to find where the fort was located. Even though they might not have found the exact place, they found near it. Today, groups of archeologists find 1 million artifacts from Fort James a year.              George Washington was a heroic leader and it's so fascinating to learn about his life, where he got is ideas, and where he lived. The land George and his family lived on is called Ferry Farm and families have lived on that land for over 12000 years. Ferry Farm is a perfect place to build a home, and that's probably why George's father moved his family there. George moved to Ferry Farm when he was only six, that means he spent almost his whole life on that land. Nobody knows exactly where the house was, nor which main farm was his, but we can use artifaccts to make an educated guess. The first buildings and floors they found were slave quarters, the kitchen, and storage houses. Occurding to records,it had said that the Washingtons' house had caught on fire. With that information, when the archeologists found burnt potterey, they had a more educated guess on where the Washingtons had built there house. They also already knew that George had smoked clay pipes, so when they found half of a clay pipe, they had a better guess on which was his house and farm. This is how we know and continue to learn so much about George Washington and his family.                Artifacts are used by archeologists so they can find information from our history. As they keep digging, we keep learning all of the amazing facts about our history. Archeologists have such an important job in our world. The job of an archeologist is to dig up the past and get the information we need to know about our history and historical figures in our history.

Item_Response: Who finds all these interesting artifacts for museums? In the articles, 'Finding Fort James', and 'Digging up George Washington's Past', by Cheryl Bradley and Gloria Corres, it explains what the finders of artifacts, or archeologists do. Archeologists have complicated, time consuming jobs, but it is all worth it to find impressive artifacts that tell us about our past.          To begin, the work that archeologists do is usually complicated. One team creates a map with 3D computer that tracks what is underground. The other team digs with a small, flat, and sharp shovel. They then put the soil in a box. The archeologists can also use a process called troweling, where they use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to get rid of dirt.           Another idea is that it is worth all this hard work. With all this work, archeologists can help people learn more about our past. In 'Digging up George Washington's Past', it explains that with all their hard work, United State's citizens have a better understanding of what he was like before he was famous, we get to know more about why he made the decisions he did, and we also get to know how Colonial Americans lived.           Lastly, their jobs are very time consuming. It took two weeks for archeologists to dig up a 25 square foot place! It also took 5 years to find James Fort!          Overall, an archeologists job is complicated, time consuming, but worth it. Even though with all this hard work archeologists work hard.

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is very interesting and fun.The many things that an archeologist do for example      find things in the ground that other people don't and it tells us about our past  for example when a group of people interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project.The first objects were found in 1861.Over 100 years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built began.The National Park Service led a five-year study of the area to figure out how the land was used.That's when they finally found James Fort! The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground.They made maps and found out that the fort stretched all the way to the river.There were ledges that were designed to hold cannons.Today, the group finds nearly 1 million objects each year.It is exciting to discover objects that were regularly used by people who lived hundreds of years ago.                     Another example of what archeologist do is when archeologists found things about George Washington like   when archeologist found that people had lived on the land known as Ferry Farm for over 12,000 years.No one knew  exactly where the Washington home was located since the actual building was long gone. At least four other houses have been built on the Ferry Farm land, so the diggers needed to find proof that this was George Washington's farmhouse.They also found part of a clay pipe we know that Washington smoked clay pipes, so this discovery gives more proof it is the right house.

Archeologists                                       By: Zhiarrize ly Rosimo                                                Have you ever wondered how we know about the people in the past and  how they lived and worked ? How we knew dinosaurs that lived here before us ? Well, we know these things because of archeologists. They are the ones who dig up these artifacts and study them. Archeologists have lots of jobs.                    First, one job an archeologist might have is that they have to find an interest that people have from the past that  can not be proved like how people were interested in studying the past of the Jamestown Rediscovery Archeological Project. When they find an interest they look for the spot where it might be. They also check if any other archeologists from the past had found artifacts that are part of the interest such as the Jamestown where archeologists found objects in the area in 1861. Then they get ready to dig the site or area . That is the first step.                     Next, before they can dig  they must find the spot where it might be. They also might find  out how the land was used  and how they used resources to find the right spot. As an example; like when the National Park led a 5 year study of the area to figure out how the land was used for the Jamestown Project. To find the right spot and area they use technology to make an image such as computer mapping software and 3D computers that can track what is underground.The information is stored away and recorded so the archeologists know what the area looked  like before they started digging.This the second step.                       Finally, they do the actual digging of the site. Another team does the real digging of the artifacts because of the computers and the technology they use the archeologists know right where to dig and what artifacts to expect. The area they do the actual digging is called the dig. They use skim shovels to start the digging of the dig.The shovels are very small ,flat, and sharp  so that they can remove the thin layers of soil , one at a time. The soil that has been dug is placed in a box with a 1/2 inch screen  in the bottom. It lets the soil fall out but the artifats stay in. They also use the process called troweling . Troweling is when the archeologists use tiny shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove the soil. This process takes a lot of hard work and time. It can take up 2 weeks just to dig a  25- square -foot section! Another team of archeologists study the artifacts at a lab and that can take a long time. The tools used by archeologists are; pick and shovel, whisk and dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel and teh trowel.                          So say thank you to your fellow archeologists because without them you would not know anything about dinosaurs or our presidents, anything because they work very hard an take their time for us to know about history. Those are the jobs of the archeologists.

Item_Response: Archeologists        The job of an archeologist is fun but can be very hard. An archeologists job is to uncover things from the past that could tell the history of something or how something lived. You would have to be very careful if you are an archeologist because you don't want to break anything.            There are lots of tools that an archeologist could use. Here are the tools that an archeologist would possibly use:   Pick and Shovel. These tools are used to dig dirt and are the tools that archeologists usually start their work with. Whisk and Dustpan. These tools are used to brush off small amounts of dirt without breaking the object. Knife. This tool is used to dig around the objects and to scrape dirt from the artifact. Wheelbarrow. A wheelbarrow is used to carry heavy objects and dirt around. Skim Shovel. This shovel is used to take thin layers of dirt. Trowel. This tool is used for scrape and cut soil to see the different types.            Archeologists can dig up small and big things. For example when the archeologists were digging up things from Fort James, they found lots of small things like the things that people threw away many years ago. Big things were found when the archeologists were trying to find out where George Washington lived. They found the stone base. That was probably huge!!!            An archeologists job is hard and sometimes takes years to finish digging up one thing. You have to be very careful when you are digging up things. But once you are finished digging up something, even if it takes a long time, it is worth it.

What is an archeologist? An archeologist, is a name for a scientists that study objects from the past. The tools they used were a pick and shovel,whisk and dustpan,a knife,skim shovel,and a trowel. If you want to ' Get Involved' then you can go to Ferry Farm, it has lot of chances to explore sites (digging sites), know how colonial life was like, and even become a junior archeologist! Why is it so important that  they found Washington's house? Well it because now we know more about are  beloved(first) president,before he became president.                                         When they first found  James Fort,they found a set of  marks on the ground,thats were they marked the walls. They also found 11 cellars,tons of burial sites,and 10 buildings in the borderd of the fort. Today groups find nearly 1 million things each year. that includes pottery,tools, coins,and even a metal toy for kids. Fact,in the 1600's they used an unused well or a big pit to throw there trash down into,settlers threw away bones from animals they ate. With that info got from those things we now know how the people in James Fort lived.                                                                The things they used were pick and shovel , whisk and dustpan,knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and a trowel. Pick and shovel, used to dig into the the earth ,close to artifacts. Whisk and dustpan, used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site. Knife, used to careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts.Wheelbarrow, used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away from excavation site.Skim shovel , a shovel  with a flate edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.Trowel,used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.                                   James Fort was built in 1607 when people came from England to start a new life. For over 200 years people thouht that  the fort was washed away by the river. But thanks to archeologist they actuly found James Fort . Now we can get to know more about how the people lived at James Fort. The natinoal park service led a 5 year study to figure out how the land was used. They knew that that would help them look for proof of the fort. People doing the study computer maping software to make an image of the area.                                                                                        To discover objects from people who lived 100s of years ago is exciting. It ties us to the people who first started the American colonies and gives us a pice of our past.

Item_Response: Hi, I'm Brady and today I would like to tell you about the United States past. People have been living here since and archeologist like me are here to discover it. Being an archeologist is hard work. You work for hours a day. You have to have gentle hands to do the job that we do. Hope you enjoy me telling you about the past and the discoveries that archeologists have made.                       The first thing I should probably tell you is what kind of tools we use to find these artifacts.Some of the tools we use a lot in beginning of the dig are the pick and the shovel. We use these to dig into the earth and get closer to the artifacts. Then we use the wheel barrow to remove the dirt that we just dug up with the shovel and pick. We also use the wheel barrow to remove the artifacts that we dug up. After that we use the skim shovel and the trowel. We use the skim shovel to remove thin layers of dirt gently and we use the trowel to scrape and view the different kinds of soils. Then some of the last tools we use are the whisk and dustpan, and the knife. We use the whisk and dustpan to remove dirt from the artifacts and we use the knife to carefully dig and to scrape the dirt from the artifacts. Those are some of the tools we use when we are out on the job and now you can see how many tools we have to use before we actually get the artifactt.               Now I am going to tell you some of the famous people that we have tried to learn more about. One of them wasn't actually a person it was a huge group of people. They lived in the Fort James in James Town. In 1994 people interested in the past started a rediscovery of Fort James. It was built in 1607 and for over 200 years people have thought that it was washed away by a river. After a few years they finally fond there first artifact in 1861 and national park services led a five-year of the area to find out how it was used. Later they found 11 cellars, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings all within the forts boundries. Then they found out that they built stone bridges going across the river and they held cannons. Back then they had wells that they would throw there trash into and and after a few years of looking for one they found it with bones from the animals they ate and the trash they threw away.Today they find nearly 1 million artifacts including pottery, tools, coins, and even a few metal toys for kids. These artifacts helped us learn a lot about the first succesful settlement.                    Another really famous person that we tried to find out more about was George Washington. Most of what we already new about him was from his time of being a soldier and his time of being  president. George Washington moved to Ferry Farm at the age of 6 and archeoligists like my self beleived that the stone base of his house was still there, so they started looking for it in 2003. It took several years to find, but eventuallly they found some of it. They found the slave quarters, the kitchen, and storage houses. Later they found the main farm house. The finding of these artifacts have us discover many things of what people did in the past and soon people will be looking for our bones.                      In conclusion, I hope you have learned many things and that you just got a chance to imagine what it is like for archeologists.   Now when all of these archeologists that you see today are dead you will take there place and keep on learning about our past.

Item_Response: The Job of a Archeologist                                                  by Sami Small       Being an archeologist is hard work. They have to use special tools like the pick and shovel in which they use to dig up the hard ground at the site. That is one of the different tools that the archeologists use wile finding artifacts.     There are different types of tools for digging up artifacts and here they are and how they are used.    The Whisk and Dustpan: used for cleaning dust and dirt off the artifact.   The Knife: used for careful digging and to help clean off the object.   The Trowel: used to scrape and cut the soil to see the different layers.   The Skim Shovel: has flat edge and is used to carefully dig a thin layer of  soil (dirt) with every scoop.   The Wheelbarrow: used to move big dirt piles and heavy artifacts.     Archeologists find different and really exiting things wile digging up artifacts. Once in 1994 they found Fort James!! Then in 2004 the archeologists found George Washington's farmhouse from when he was a kid!!! They found out that the kitchen, slave quarters,  storage houses, and farmhouse were seperate buildings.     There are different places to go on the enternet to find what archeologists have learned and found here are four I think might give the most information about finding George Washington's farmhouse:   http://www.smithsonianmag.com/history-acheology/digs-washington-200809.html?c=yge=1 or http://www.kenmore.org or http://diganthro.wordpress.com/ferry-farm or http://www.uwlax.edu/mvac/ProcessArch/ProcessArch/field_excavationtech.html with these you can learn all about how they found the stone base of Washington's house. Then if you want to learn about how they found Fort James here are three websites I found that might give you some infomation:   http://www.nps.gov/jame/historyculture/chronology-of-jamestown-archeology.html or http://historicjamestowne.org or http://apva.org/rediscovory with these you can learn about how they found james fort.

Item_Response: If I were an archeologist I would spend my whole digging up important information. I might find golden coins.Or might find bullets from World War II or III. The tools I would use is a pick and shovel, a whisk a dustpan, and a knife, because a pick is used to cut into cement. A shovel is used dig into sand and soil. A whisk is to brush off artifacts. Other tools I would use is a wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and a trowel. A wheelbarrow is used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away from the excavation site. I would use a skim shovel because it removes a little bit of soil at a time. And I would use a trowel because it is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil. That is why I would use these tools.

Item_Response: The Search of James Fort   By: Sami Siddiqui       Introduction: How the Topic Started       A gang of people were fascinated to start the Jamestown rediscovery Archeological Project. The activity is used to explore the hidden secrets of James Fort of Jamestown, Virginia. A rumor spread that a river washed away for the past 200 years. Still, a few clues have been found, which made people think that it is still standing.       Brief History of James Fort       The fort was designed in 1607 at the time when English people settled in the colonies to start their lives again. Many people thought that fort was built near a river to have simple docking. Archeologists later found artifacts that led them into a wrong course. The spot for the fort was clever because it kept more protection of enemy ships.                The Reasearch       The first few items were found in 1861. The revealed objects were a few swords and suits of armor. Archeologists also found floors of buildings. Many, many years later, clues led to where the fort was located.   The National Park Service were paying much attention to the fort. The people were imaging the area to be sure the area was correct.       The Founding of James Fort       It turned out to be right! The James Fort was actually found! The archeologists left tracings and markings so the location can be found many times again and again. Maps were developed, and evidence was shown that the fort was built by the river. The archeologists uncovered 11 cellars, many burial sights, and ten buildings constructed by the fort!       Conclusion        In conclusion, James Fort is a mysterious place that had covered secrets found by the archeologists. In my opinion, James fort is an interesting place to learn and study about.

Item_Response: The job of an Archeologist can be very hard. Being an archeologist means you dig up parts of the past. In the sources 'Finding Fort James' and 'Digging up George Washington's Past' the author explains how an archeologist's job is.       First a group of archeologists use computer to make a image of the dig site. The archeologist then go out and mark the site with flags. they then call up a different group of archeologist to start the dig.       They start the dig with Picks And Shovels. Then as they get deeper they use Skim Shovels and Trowels. They also use wheelbarrows to haul the dirt away. When they reach the artifacts they use Whisks and Dustpans to get the artifacts clean then they use knifes to get dirt out of small places.       Lastly the artifacts go to the last group of archeologist to be looked at. This group makes such it is an artifact. If it is not an artifact they throw it away. If it is it is sent to a museum.       To conclude being an archeologist is a hard job but can make you rich or famous.

Item_Response: Wouldn't you love to travel around the world to discover the lives of famous people that are not alive anymore, firsthand? Archeologists are experts on finding, cleaning, and analyzing ancient artifacts, and other things left behind by ancient people and learn what their lives used to be like. These experts use many tools to help them find these amazing treasures.       To begin, the first stage of extracting an operation is using computer software to map the contents of the ground. These models are helpful towards the teams that will later come and dig up the site. This is important, so people can know where all the artifacts are, and what structures the project might interfere with.       To continue, after the teams who map the area are finished with their part of the job, the team that will do the actual digging come. This team begins by first using small, sharp, and thin shovels called skims to carefully remove the many layers of the dirt. After completing that, the diggers start a process called troweling. This process is carried out with shovels wooden picks to remove more layers of the soil. The entire process of digging can take up to two entire weeks, just for a small 25 square foot section of the soil. This stage is hard, and tedious, but it is one of the most important stages of the large job.       The final stage of the tiresome (but fun) process that archeologists carry out is analyzing the artifacts that were found by the digging team. Technicians spent lots of time to use their expensive equipment to complete the hard work the two other teams did, and actuly learn from the many artifacts found. After many months of hard work, analyzing is complete. The long job has been ended, and all the teams, and all of the other scientists become thankful for the important information the hark work of the many archeologists has found.       To conclude, becoming an archeologist is a painful, but fun, process which helps everyone discover important things in the covered past. Archeologists are important people because of what they discover. Maybe one day, you would love to become a famous time-traveler!

Item_Response: The Life of an Archeologist                    Being an archeologist is an interesting job. When they are working, they need to be delicate when handling object on their site. Even though it seems uninteresting, it still is fun. Few archeologists have struck it rich during their job. That is why so many people are archeologists.               An archeologist needs to be delicate. They also have delicate tools. First they use the pick and shovel. That is used to dig into the earth. Once you get close to the artifact, you would use a Skim Shovel. It has a flat edge that can easily dig out a thin layer of dirt. If there is any excess dirt, an archeologist can use a wheelbarrow to take the dirt away. When you have hit the object, you can use the Trowel. It can remove small parts of dirt. When you have dug out the object, use the Knife and the Whisk to brush and clean the artifact.               When they are on the site, the archeologist uses the Skim Shovel to dig. Then, they put the soil in a box with a screen that lets the dirt fall out. Then they study the object. Everything takes a lot of patience and work but once you find something, it is worth it.               Being an archeologist is fun because there is always the chance that you will get rich and helps historians learn more. It also teaches you a lot. Being an archeologist is truly a great job.

Digging in the dirt will give you dusty jeans but also a lot of valuable items or artifacts that you may find.   They use a wheelbarrow to move items from one place to another.   Knifes are used for digging also you have to be really careful though.   The trowel are the most common  tool in archeology. They are used to scrape and cut  to view layers of soil.

Item_Response: Being an Archeologists is a interesting,and hard job. Every year there are several teams with 35 people in it. One team uses 3D computers that can show you what is underground. So archeologists would know where they could dig. The second team has to dig holes. It takes them two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section.         Archeologists start to dig the holes with skim shovels. Skim shovels are small, flat and sharp and they can remove thin layers of soil. The soil is placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. This lets the dirt fall out.        The diggers also use a process called troweling. Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt. Another team spends days in the labs studying the objects that are found. The whole procces is slow and vtiresome, but it's worth it.

Item_Response: This informational report will be about Archeology and Archeologists. It will explore what Archeologists do, what they dig up, and how they dig them up. This report can explain why Archeology is good and why we need it. The research is extremely helpful, so we need to thank our archeologists for working hard.         Archeologists are people who dig up things from the past, or artifacts as they are scientifically called. Archeologists work on teams of up to 35 people. They can dig up artifacts and begin to know more about history.        There are several ways of digging up artifacts. But first you might want to have a specific idea of what you are looking for. Maybe you could do some research within the area? One way of digging up artifacts is using a pick and a shovel to get closer to the ground where artifacts might lay. Another way is using a trowel or a skim shovel to remove, scrape, or cut layers of soil. You can just keep doing that until you find artifacts. Once you have found them, you can use a whisk and a dust pan to brush away the dirt on the artifacts. There are many more ways of digging up artifacts, but these are the most common.         Archeology is a very helpful thing. We can learn many things about history from what Archeologists find. It helps to know more about history because we can understand how life was a long time ago and try to make the present world better than it was then.         It takes a long time to go through the entire process. First, you need to know where you are going to look or what you are going to look for. Then you need to begin digging, or finding artifacts. Next, (If you have found any artifacts) you need to try to figure out what it is and then clean it off good. Now you are an Archeologist! This process can be very tiresome and can get you pretty dirty, but it's all worth it.        Now you know what it is like studying Archeology and being an Archeologist. It can be difficult, but it is all worth it in the long run! Understand that Archeology can help us humans learn more about history!

Item_Response: Archeologists Historical Discoveries               This research will be about archeologists historical discoveries. They will be finding Fort James, digging up George Washington's past,finding the spot of Ferry Farm, and the tools used.                            In the year of 1994, a group of people were going to study the past that had started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project or J.R.A.P. This project has been designed to discover secrets of James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. For more than 2 centuries, people thought that Fort Jamestown was washed away by a river. A couple of discoveries in that area made a hint that it may still be around. The first discoveries were found in the year of 1861. The archeologists that were studying the Jamestown Fort found uncovered armor and weapons. Some also found the floors of buildings. Over a century later, a group found the exact spot where the fort was built.           A lot of what we know about George Washington comes from the time when he was a soldier and our first president. Biographies barely have any information about George Washington's life as a child. That has changed. There has been recent discoveries about where Washington's childhood home is and how it has helped historians learn more about our first president's history as a child.           Lots of people have lived on the land where Ferry Farm once was for over 12,000 years! That is a long time. The location of Ferry Farm makes the land a perfect place to build a home for families. However, it is no surprising that George Washington's father, Augustine Washington, moved his family there. At that time George was just 6 years old! Because the actual building was long gone, no one knew exactly where the Washington's home was located.         The tools that were used by the Archeologists to find their discoveries such as George Washington's home were used carefully,so that the objects that were found wouldn't break, because they were very old. These tools are, pick and shovel. (Most digs start with these two tools. Used to dig into the earth, close to artifacts.) Whisk and dustpan.(Used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away from the excavation site.) The knife. (Used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts.) The wheelbarrow. (Used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away from the excavation site.) The skim shovel. (A shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.) Last but not least, the trowel. (Probably the most common tool in archeology. Used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.)           Throughout this research a lot has been learned. In this research archeologists have found Fort James. they have dug up George Washington's past. They have found the spot of Ferry Farm. They also have used very important tools for these discoveries. That is the end of this research on Archeologists Historical Discoveries.

Item_Response: The history of Fort James and George Washington's past       in 1994 a group of people was intrested in studying the past in jamestown.For 200 years people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river.Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around. The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life.   Objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away from a river.The new spot probaly gave the settlers more protection from enemy ships.The first object foun in 1861.Archeologists uncovered armor and weapons they also discovered the floors of buildings.Over 100 years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built.The first thing they found was a set of the marks on the ground and they showed where the fort's walls used to be.They made maps and found out that the fort stretched all the way to the river then they relized there were stone ledges built over the river.The ledges were designed to hold cannons and the archeologists found 11 cellers, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings all within the border of the fort.Today the groups finds more than 1 million objects a year the objects include pottery,tools,coins,and even metal toys for children.The information learned from these objects helps us understand how the people in the james fort lived.We now know the settlers fought the Powhatan tribethat often attacked them.

Item_Response: A job for an archeologist seems very complicated. For those of you who have no idea what an archeologist is, well, I'll tell you. Archeologists are people who dig in the ground to find artifacts.There are many reasons for how a life of an archeologist can be complicated.           Firstly, being an archeologist takes a lot of skill. They have to dig without damaging anything. You also need to have the right tools to dig into the ground. For example, if you needed a trowel but used a knife, that wouldn't be right to use. Pursuing this further, an archeologist has to have knowledge. They have to be smart and know where to go and to dig. For example, if you wanted to find out about Abraham Lincoln and you were nowhere near where he lived, you won't find anything from him! Finally, an archeologist has to have patience. They must be careful and slow at their process. For example, if you dig, whisk, and wheelbarrow fast, you may not have the most clean artifact.   There are some reasons how an archeologist's life can be complicated.

Item_Response: Archeologists use many tools on the dig.  One is a pick and shovel, it is used to start the dig and get close to the artifacts.        The next tool is a whisk and dustpan, they are used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear the dig.         A knife is used for careful digging.         A wheelbarrow is used to move items and dirt away from the dig.          The skim shovel is a flat edge used to carefully remove thin layers of dirt.          The last tool is a trowel,  it is probably the most common used tool.  It is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.  The archeologists have started many camps for kids to come and explore what it is like to be an archeologist.

Item_Response: Archeologists           Archaeologists have so much work. They search new things to make their history. They can answer most of the history of the past. It is an exiting to discover people and things which were hundred years ago. It gives us a piece of our past and tells us how are we like this and who started the American colonies.            What we know about George Washington comes from his time as a solder and president. The archeologists know all this by digging up the past by tools. They use important tools like pick and shovel for start to dig or to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts, whisk and dustpan used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site, knife used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts, wheelbarrow to take dirt away from site, skim shovel is a shovel with a flat edge used to dig away thin layer, trowel used to view the different layers of soil.           There can be up to 35 people in a team. The first team maps the area using 3D computers to track underground. This helps people know how did it look like before before people starting digging. Another team focuses on actual digging. Those archeologists start digging with skim shovels. The soil is then then placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. The diggers also use a process called troweling. Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt. It can take up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section! Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found. The whole process is slow and tiresome, but it's worth it.           I think the archeologists jobs are interesting. I think most people will chose that job, but i would choose another job because I have interests in that.

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist             You may stop and think, 'What is the use of an archeologist?'. A lot of people think that archeologists are of no use. Sure, the job is tiring and slow. But it's worth it. Today I will explain why archeologists are important and what they do during the job. I will also explain how archeologists find information about ancient people and my opinion on archeologists.              Archeologists may seem useless because all they do every day is just dig and look for buried things in the ground all day long. It may seem like that but their job is actually very useful to the world. Looking at source #2, it says 'Most of what we know about George Washington comes from his time as a soldier and president. Biographies don't have very much information about his childhood.' People don't have much information about his childhood but thanks to archeologists, that's changing. Archeologists dig in places where George lived as a child to find out what kind of life he led when he was young. Aren't you curious to find out about this great American's childhood? Thanks to present archeologists we are finding more about George Washington's life everyday. It is not just George Washington however, it is also to find out more events from the past of a lot of famous people. From source #1, archeologists have found more information about Fort James. Archeologists are still studying ancient people and let's hope we can find more about more famous people. That is the use of an archeologist. To find out more about famous people. Now you know the use of an archeologist.             To find out information of an ancient person, archeologists use lots of tools. Archeologists work in teams that can hold up to 35 people. Lots of teams work together on a site. This is what archeologists do when trying to dig. The first team maps the area with 3D computers that can track what is underground. The information is recorded so that people will know what the area looked like before people started digging. Another team that is called a dig, does the digging in the area. They first use skim shovels that are so small, flat, and sharp, that they can remove thin layers of soil, one at a time. The soil is then placed in a box that has a half-inch screen at the bottom. This lets the dirt fall out while the artifacts stay in. The digs use another process called troweling. Troweling is a process that archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove the dirt out of artifacts. Surprisingly, it takes 2 weeks to dig up a 25-square-foot section! The final team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found. This whole process is slow and tiresome, but it's worth it if it's to shape history. Now you know how hard it is to find historical artifacts. The whole thing is so slow that you need to have a lot of patience if you want to be an archeologist. This is how people dig up the past.              'How do archeologists find out about events in history when all they're doing is looking at objects?'. That might be a question frequently asked and here's the answer. Looking at sources #1 and 2, They found lots of things left behind in the ruins of James Fort and George Washington's childhood home. The pieces of burnt pottery they found at Ferry Farm showed that there was a fire there and the metal toys they found at Fort James proved that there were children there. Looking and studying these things actually tell you how people lived in those days. That is how people find out how ancient humans lived in those times.             I think that an archeologists job is fun, even though you need to have a lot of patience. Digging and studying ancient artifacts that have been touched by famous people would also make me feel special. I think that an archeologist's job is very fun and I would love to do it.             Now you know all about the job of an archeologist. I hope this essay has been of use to you. Thank you for reading this!

Item_Response: There is a day called History Day were all the kids look for things that they don't know.           Once a group of people that were interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. But the project had been designed to discover the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown Virginia. For over 200 years people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river. Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around.        But the fort was built in 1607 when the settlers came from England to start a new life the kids thought that was really interesting. Most believed that the James fort was built near the river. It was easier to dock ships there so it made sense that the settlers would choose that spot. But however objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away. The new spot probably gave the settlers more protection from enemy ships the kids that are looking for some things that they don't know about it looks like they get allot of information that tells them allot about what happened back then.   And the first objects were found in 1861. Archeologists are the names for scientists who study objects from the past uncovered armor and weapons. They also discovered the floors of buildings. Over 100 years later a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort had been built.               Now the National Park Service led a five-year study of the whole area to figure out how that land was used. They knew that this would help them decide where to look for proof of the fort. The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area.               That's when they finally found James Fort!!! The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground. The marks showed where the Fort's walls used to be. Between all the stories they heard and read about and drawings they made the archeologists knew that the fort would be shaped like a triangle. They made maps and found out that the fort stretched all the way to the river. Then they realized there were stone ledges built over the river. The ledges were designed to hold canons. The archeologists also found eleven cellars dozens of burial sites and ten buildings all within the border of the fort ground.           And the group of kids are going to find one million objects each year. The objects include pottery, tools, coins,and even metal toys for children. In the 1600s, people used to throw their trash down an unused well or into a big pit. While digging in the area the archaeolists found the trash the settlers threw away including the bones of animals they ate. The information learned from these objects helps us understand how the people settlers fought the Powhatan tribe that often attacked them.
