Item_Response: about Archeologist and what they do and how they do their job                          A archeologist has a veary important job. a archeologist finds valubale artifacts that were used a long time ago and then studys these artifacts to learn about what it was used for or how it worked or even find oud whose it was. If we did not have archeologist we would not know a whole lot of things like slavory or Fort James or veary important things that happend in history like the Reviutioary War. Each group of archeologist has up to 35 people on a team. The first team mapes the area using a 3D imige on a computer and then they can see what is under ground so that they know where to dig and some what of a imige if what they will try to find. Then the teams spred out and start to dig and hope the will find what they are looking for. After a long long time of digging and searching for this object and they find the object they are looking for they will send it to another group of people who will study the object this prosses could take years to finish but these people will continue to this over and over again.           Tools Used By Archeologists           One of the main tools used by a archeologist is a pickaxe and a shovel these tools are used to start digging into the ground. The pickaxe is used to brack through stone and the shovel is used to did through the dirt. A whist and dust pan is another inportant tool. This tool is used when you find a inportant artifact in the ground. The whist is used to brush off the dirt and the pan is used to move the dirt that is put into the pan. A knife is one other tool archeologist use when the find a artifact in the ground. If the whist and pan dont work the knife is used to scrape of the remaning dirt. The wheel barrle is another common tool in a work site. It is used to move the dirt or stone that is dug out on the ground while triying to find the important artifacts. A skim shovel is just like a regular shovel but thinner. The skim shovel is used to take off thinner layers of dirt. Item_Response: The Job of an Archaeologist   What is an archaeologist? An archaeologist is a person who studies objects from the past. They use many different tools such as pickaxe, shovel, whisk, dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and a trowel.              Archaeologists dig up artifacts from the past to try and figure out how they lived, what they ate, and where their houses were. Once they had found the artifacts they would take the to the lab and study what they were, what they were used for and what they are made out of.              When I had listed the tools  above I will now tell you about them. The pickaxe they would use to dig through hard surfaces. The shovel would be used for digging through softer surfaces such as dirt and mud. Whisks would be used for dusting off the artifacts and a dustpan would be used for sweeping things into it. A wheelbarrow would be used for moving piles of dirt and other things to different places. A knife would be for scraping dirt away from the artifacts. A skim shovel would be for removing thin layers of the earth. And last but not least a trowel would be to scrape and cut to see different layers of earth. The archaeologists would  use different equipment to draw maps of the areas and guess about what might have been there many many years ago.

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist          An archeologist studies objects from the past.  They use different tools to find objects from the past.  These objects are called artifacts.  Archeologists have found many artifacts.          Some artifacts archeologists find are sometimes places or buildings.  In 1944, a group of people intrested in the past stated the Jamestown Rediscovery Archeological Project.  Their project was to find James Fort in Jamestown, which people thought washed away by a river.  James Fort was built in 1607 by colonists.  They built near a river so it was easier to dock ships.  But, with the artifacts found, it is hinted that Fort James was located further away.  Some of the first artifacts they found were armor and weapons.  They had also found floors of the buildings.  Over a century later, a group effort to find the correct location of Fort James began.  The National Park Service` led a five-year study of the area to find out how the land was used. This would help them find proof of the fort.  The people doing the study used a computer mapping software to make an image of the area.  That's when they found James Fort.  After finding James Fort they also found cellars burial sites and buildings within the border of the fort.          Another place archeologists dug for is George Wasington childhood home. Washington's home was built on Ferry Farm, but no one knows exactly where it was located.  However, archeologists believed there was a stone base under the house.  They started digging in  2003.  It took over a year, but they found Washington's childhood farmhouse.  They also found the kitchen, slave quarters, and storage houses.            Tools used by archeologists are pickaxes, shovels, whisks, dustpans, knives, skim shovels, and trowels.  The pickaxe and shovel are used in the beginning of the dig to dig near artifacts. Whisks and dustpans are used to brush away dirt from the artifacts and the excavation sites.  The knife is used for careful digging and to scrape dirt off of the artifacts.  Wheelbarrows are used to carry dirt and items from one place to another.  Skim shovels have a flat edge to carefully remove a thin layer of dirt with each scoop.  Trowel is the most commonly used tool in archeology. it is used to scrape and and cut to view layers of soil.          These are what past archeologists did, found, and used.

Item_Response: To be an archeologist                     To be an archeologist would be an exciting job to have. You would be able to find new things. Item_Response: I think the job of an archaeologist is exciting. What an archaeologist does is they find a excavation site about someone or something that interests them and go to that site. Once they are there, they use special laptops with sonar equipment to track what's underground. Once they know where it is, they start to dig with either their shovel or pickax. Once their nice and close to the artifact(s), they use their skim shovel, knife, whisk, and trowel to carefully get to an object. Item_Response: ARCHEOLOGISTS          An archeologist is a person who goes around the world uncovering the past. An archeologist often maps out their dig site with computer before digging. Archeologists help us learn more about our culture and past. They go where some don't and dig up things others wouldn't. Item_Response: The job of an archeologists can be difficult. An archeologist has to lots of patience because they must wait a long time before they start finding things. Also archeologists must work really hard looking for artifacts.       They must use different types of tools on their dig sites. The first two are a pick and shovel. These are used to dig close to where they know artifacts are laying. The next two are a whisk and dustpan these are used to brush dirt away from the artifacts. The next two are the knife and wheelbarrow. The knife is used for careful digging and also to scrape dirt from around artifact sand the wheelbarrow is used to carry dirt away from the dig.The last two are the skim shovel which is a shovel with a flat edge that is used to remove a thin layer of dirt with each scoop and a trowel which you would use to scrape and cut to view different layers of dirt.         Archeologists must be good at using and understanding computers because they have to use computers to make graphs on the area they are excavating. They must also have to be able to focus on one thing for a long period of time. If they are looking for artifacts on certain people they would have to know what happened through the course of their life so they know what to look for. If they were looking for bones or a dinosaur then they would have to know what the skeletal structure of different dinosaurs.       There are different jobs on a dig site there is a team that digs and there is another team that's in charge of mapping out the dig sites and dealing with computers. There can be up thirty-five people on a team at one time. It's important that everyone does there job or else all the work won't get done. Different people are probably put on different teams because they have different strengths.

Item_Response: I believe that archeologists jobs are to find artifacts from places that are important in our history, such as presidents houses, or forts from previous wars. They can find these artifacts to learn more about these important events, or people. Them finding these objects can also help us understand more about the lives of historical people. And, if they think something in history was incorrect, archeologists could assure that its correct, by finding the locations and artifacts from the event they think is incorrect, and find the truth.           In 1861, there were the first objects found in Jamestown by archeologists. Around 100 years later, a different group began to search for the exact location of the James Fort. They believed it was located near a river, so it would be easier to dock ships there. However, in 1994, archeologists began searching again in Jamestown for the James Fort, which people believed for many years that it was washed away by the river they thought it was near. By judging the objects that they found close to the river, the archeologists thought that it was located somewhere farther away from the river, so they were safer from any enemies. They finally found Jamestown by looking at a group of marks on the ground, and decided that it was triangular, and was located near the edge of the river. Now the archeologists find many artifacts near where the fort really is.           Many archeologists wanted to learn more about the home of George Washington, because they didn't know much about his childhood. They knew that the Washington's lived on the Ferry Farm, and moved there when he was six years old. Although they didn't know the exact location of the house, they began to dig in 2003 at the Ferry Farm. It took more than a year when they finally found the Washington's home. They found the kitchen, storage houses and slave quarters first, then years later, found the main farmhouse. Archeologists said there were other houses built on the Ferry Farm, so they needed the proof that it was really George Washington's childhood farmhouse. They said that there was a fire at his house, because they dug up some burnt pottery, along with part of a pipe. Which was more proof that it was the Washington home, because George smoked.           People wonder how the archeologists found all those objects from the Ferry Farm. Well, what they do is form a few groups of up to 35 people to dig. They use 3D computers and machines to track underground, and find artifacts, this is so the diggers know where to look and what it will look like. Some archeologists focuses on the real digging, with a type of shovel called a skim shovel. They are small and very flat, therefore they can dig the layers one at a time. Others will place the soil into a box with a small screen at the bottom, which lets the dirt fall out, and the artifacts, if any, stay in. They also use many other tools, for troweling, such as small shovels, paint brushes and wooden picks to remove any dirt covering the objects. There are other archeologists that take the artifacts to a lab to study them. It can take a while to dig up a section. Up to two weeks for just 25-square-foot area!

Item_Response: The job of an archaeologist sounds like lots of fun! But when I tell you about all of the work they do what would you think? would you think that it is more fun, or boring? lets find out.       The job of an archaeologist is to inform the world by finding artifacts for hundreds of years ago. Some of the things archaeologists do are really fun. Some of the tools they use are the pickaxe, shovel, whisk, dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and trowel. sometimes archaeologists have to go to different countries to find artifacts! Do you still think that the job of an archaeologist is boring?       I don't think it is, because it sounds fun to be able to go around the world just for work! Want to know more? Here is what each of the tools do. The pick and shovel are obviously used for digging down to the artifacts. the whisk and dustpan are use to brush and clear dirt. the knife is used for carefully digging and scraping dirt from the excavation site. the wheelbarrow is used for moving items from one site to another. the skim shovel is used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop. And last but not least the trowel, which is used for scraping and cutting to view the different layers of soil.

Item_Response: An archeologist's job is to find and recover items from the past, or artifacts. Archeologists most likely work in groups, rather than working by themselves. They work like this because the artifacts are very delicate historical items, and all of these items are crucial to discovering the history of mankind. Archeologists hold a lot of responsibility to keep the artifacts safe, clean, and whole.       While working, an archeologist needs many tools. Here are some of the tools that an archeologist might use in their work: a pick and shovel (to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts), a whisk and dustpan (to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear the dirt away from the excavation site), a knife (to dig carefully and scrape dirt off the artifacts), and a wheelbarrow (to carry away dirt from the excavation site or to move something from one place to another). These tools often help archeologists in their work.       How do these archeologists find all these artifacts? The first thing they do is have one team of archeologists use 3D computers to map the area. Then the information is recorded so that people will know what it looked like before they start digging. A different team of archeologists does the actual digging, and they place where the team digs is called a dig. These archeologists start digging with skim shovels, a small, sharp, and flat shovel that can remove small layers of soil at a time. The soil that is dug up is placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. The screen lets the dirt fall out of the box, while the artifacts stay in. The digging team also does a process called troweling. What is troweling? Trowling is when the archeologists use wooden picks, paint brushes, and small shovels to get rid of dirt. All of these processes are cautious ones, and only professional archeologists should perform them.       As you can tell, an archeologist's job is tough, requires maximum intelligence, and is lined with caution. Beacause if almost anybody else finds artifacts in their backyard and trys to handle them like an archeoloist would, say good-bye to the artifact (well, say good-bye to the artifact being whole, at least). And that, kids, is why you should never dig for artifacts in your backyard!

Item_Response: An Archeoligist's Job                What An Archeoligist Will Need?                                                                              To dig or to find something that you are in luck of looking for you will need to have the right tools. Some of the things you willl need is a pick & a shovel to dig something up.To put all of your artifacts in you will need a wheelbarrow or you can use the wheelbarrow by puting the dirt that you dug up in the wheelbarrow so you can be tidy with the dirt.You will also need a skim shovel to carfully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop. You will also need a whisk and dustpan to scoop all of the dirt up in a nice pile.You will also need a good archeoligist group of men to carry hard and heavy things and women to get very deep in the dirt.Last you will need a knife for carfully digging and to scrape the dirt carfully of the artifacts.Those are a couple things you will need to by or have before you complete an archeoligist job.               What Kind Of Things You Will Be Instrested In Looking For?   If you are looking for something think of a great spot with dirt but a mystirious place and start just digging anything you find keep at first have fun and dig and dig and find lot's of stuff and keep and use.Second you want to get serious at your digging first you had your fun now you need to look for things that is just very strage, you would want to look up some things and places and a artifact that has not been found in 100 years go to the place and start digging with your group and when you find something take it straight back to your lab and look at it a disekt it and keep it as your First Artifact  that you have found so far because before all those things you saw and dug that was just having fun and getting the hang of it but when you found that first artifact that was just your first.                       What You Will Do When You Find A Facinating Artifact?   When you find a facinating artifact you just keep on going its the first thing its always the beginning of an areoligist process you dont just stop when you find you find a cool artifact you just wait like I said its just the beginning of an archeoligist process.When you find that arifact you never know if your going to find something bigger and better the next day.Those are things an archeoligist would do if he found a facinating artifact and he had no idea what to do with it at the time and thats the process of an acheoligist process.                                       What Can You Do If You End Up Finding Nothing In The Location Your In?    When you maybe end up finding nothing o=in your location you dont just give up the task you were looking forward into doing you just find a nother location to dig up something mysirious and weired or you can just look up some facts that explain to you what is an artifact that has not been found over than 100 years ago then it will pop up people who have tryed digging or finding this artifact you prombly will end up have a lucky chance of finding it by the process of searching those are things an archeoloigist would do if he is not finding anything in the location he is at.                           What Would You Do If You Want To Reserch Another Person?    When you feel like you are not finding the right artifacts that you are in need of finding all you need to do is reserch another task that no one has been looking for but has and thought was going to be easy but ening up be a whole diaster.And when you feel like when you serched it up think of something you've heard as a diasaster in life like the 'Titanic' you can get up some people and go to where that disaster had happend and end up finding some good artifacts.Those are a couple things an archeologist would do and say.                           How To Pick The Right Group Members To Work With During This Task?   When you are doing a task you would like to find the right group mwmbers to work with like some poeple who know how to work hard and get a task done.Or someone you know who can use a shovel good,Also someone you know who can use all the tools good like a Pick,Shovel,Skim Shovel, Trowel Or A Knife all those things but know what there doing sand know how to do it right and get down to business. or you would like to pick someone who is not sassy or bossy.And last you dont want to pick someone who is weak and not strong.Those are things and archeoligist would say.                       How To Know When Its Time To Stop The Task?   When you think the task you where working on has now been comepleted the first thing you would like to do is count how many artifacts you have the minimum is 20-40 thats all.The next thing you would want to do is skan them and see where this came from? and how it looks like? this and how it got here?.When you are done with that,thats how you know you are done with this task or when its time to stop.                           What Do You Do With The Artifacts You Found?   When you are done with the artifacts that you have found you need to take it to a museam or spit it with your group members.But what you dont do is just throw it away or keep it all to your self those are a couple things an archeoligist would do when he is done with his task.

Item_Response: What Archeologists Do                                                                                                                                                Archeologists are people who study the past. They have very creative and important jobs. They work with              finding bones of dinosaurs.They sometimes even try finding the history of a area where somewhere very important              lived. They sometimes sell the artifacts they find to museums and let all of us see their discoveries. I can tell you              what materials they use to find artifacts, what they do when they find artifacts, and what some do with them. Here              is what I know about archeologists.                                                                                    The Right Tools                          Archeologists look under the concrete and into the Earth to find what their looking for. But they need the              right tools to do that. Archeologists usually work with picks and shovels, whisk and dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow,              skim shovel, and trowel. Picks and shovels are the starting tools. Whisk and dustpans are used for when they clear              away dirt from the artifact and the site they found it. The knife is used for very careful digging. Along with scraping              dirt around the artifact.                                              Next the wheelbarrow is used to move the dirt that was already researched. Skim shovels have flat edges to               carefully remove a thin layer of soil. Lastly the trowel, the most common tool used in archeology, is used to scrape               and cut to view the layers of soil. These are the tools that archeologists use to help them identify what they have              found or what they are looking for. The best tools to use when they have found an artifact is probably whisk and              dustpan, the knife, and the trowel.                                                                                 What They Do Now                                                                                                               What do they do now they found something? They first clean off the object briefly at the site it was found.                 Then the expert does further cleaning at the lab. Once they have finished the cleansing on the object, they do closer                inspection. They look at the scratches. they reserch how old the dirt is. They figure out what could have possesed                 the artifact, either person or animal. Once they have solved all these mysteries, they sum it up. Example: they find                a foot print near a empty area of dirt where there was once a community. It was a big foot print. Could it be a huge                 footed man or a large creature foot print? They reserch until they find out. They then realize it was a large mammal                that caused it, but don't know what animal. They are still researching.                                                                                                                                                  Where They Will Go                             What do they do with their amazing discovery? They either keep for further researching the object, give it to                important people, or sell it to museums. Don't worry, they keep all of the artifact's discoveries and history to them               and a little bit to us in museums. They give it to important people, such as the military, because it could be dangerous               to all of us and the military can do something about it. They keep the artifacts to them selves for further researching               because they need to know more about it. The more research, the more we can know about the past and future.                                                                                          Conclusion                                                         This is my report of what I know on archeologists. I am glad I was able to tell you about them making very                interesting research and how important their jobs are. I hope they are as interested in their job as much as I am. This                has been my report on archeologists.

Item_Response: The amazing discovery            Just think about all the new things you will learn about old things! Well, if you are going to be an archeologist, you shall do just that! An archeologist is a scientist who studies archeology, or the study of ancient things. Being an archeologist can be boring and tiresome, but surely fun!!        The first mission to a successful archeology project, is the identification of the material. Scientists use a special computer to track down and locate the item that they want to discover. Using sophisticated radar can be helpful, they use X-ray machines. Given all these privileges, scientists get a rough idea of what the material looks like underground, so it can help them see if they have found it the right thing.         This leads to the process of digging. After they have found the item, it is time to dig it out. Here is where a LOT of what archeology means, comes into action. The digging starts with archeologists using a tool, called a Skim Shovel. These are special shovels that are small, flat, and sharp. All this makes the shovel dig out a layer of soil. The dirt is dropped into a box with a small, so that the soil can leak out by itself. Then comes a bigger tool, the shovel. This kind of shovel takes larger amounts of soil off the ground. The box will overflow, because of the bigger quantity of soil, and dirt. This drags another tool in; the wheelbarrow. A wheelbarrow is sort of like a wagon, which is essential because the soil amount has increased. When the archeologist finally hits a surface, he or she takes out the other tools for the job; the whisk and the dustpan. These are used to brush the dust off the surface so that they can see what the surface is really like. If it is the object they are looking for, they are successful.        The final and most important part of the project is researching it. After the item has been found, the scientists take it with them to their lab, to research the material. They do may tests on it, and analyze it. Archeology is a great study. So why don't you go out and start digging?

Item_Response: If there were no archeologists, we would not know the history of people who lived long time ago. It is same for places, too. This tells us that archeologist is a very important job. Then what exactly is an archeologist?     Archeologists find artifacts that once belonged to famous people, or is famous itself. We can know the history of long time ago by using the artifacts. However, archeologist is not an easy job. First they need to know where the artifact is. Then they need to find a proof that it is the right artifact. Finally, they start to dig. This steps may sound simple, but when you actually do it, it may take months and years to find an artifact.     When you are certain that an artifact is in an exact place, you need to find a proof, like I said before. For example, they found a clay pipe in a place where archeologists thought George Washington's house might be. They knew that Washington smoked clay pipes, so it gives proof that it is the right place. Then, they start to dig. Many teams will work on the site. The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground.Another team starts to dig. They start with skim shovels that remove layers of soil. The soil is placed in a box with a half- inch screen at the bottom. The dirt falls out while the artifact stays in. They also use a process called troweling, which is when you remove the dirt with small brushes and wooden picks. There are a lot more tools that are used by archeologists, but still, everything is used to dig and dig. Another team studies the objects that are found in the lab. This whole process takes a lot of time and effort.     The discovery of artifacts is really important because people can learn how people lived long time ago, and if the artifact belongs to a famous person, they can learn more about the person. Artifacts also give us a piece of our past and ties us to the people who first started the American colonies. You may think being an archeologist is a boring job, but it is actually a meaningful and important job!

Item_Response: In the articles ' Finding Fort James' and 'Digging up George Washington's Past,' by Cheryl Bradley and Gloria Corres, the authors state that archeology is a hard job and needs a lot of patience.            To begin, archeology is a process that divides between two teams. The people in the digging process have to trowel. Troweling is when archeologists use tiny tools such as small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden toothpicks to take out the dirt from the artifacts. That's one teams job. Another team is looking at the artifacts in a lab and discovering what is has to do with the life of the person. Archeologists have to work together to find the best and truthful results.             Apart of the process, the archeologists have to make sure the facts they find have a reasonable explanation. For example: George Washington's house supposedly had a fire and archeologists had found some burnt pottery proving that his house did actually have a fire. Also, around the 1860's archeologists had discovered that Fort James wasn't only next to the river, but was also farther away to protect the town from enemy ships. Archeology is a very interesting and leads to many new interesting discovery's.             Lastly, when the artifacts are proven to be true, the pieces teach humans about other humans lives. For example: George Washington's past has taught children and adults about who he really was and about his family. Also, the fort James taught how smart people were in the olden days and why they didn't live next to the harbor. Not only is being a archeologist interesting and fun, but it also teaches other people a lesson along with yourself.                   To conclude, archeology is a historical 'mystery' that teaches people about this persons life in the earlier days. It also shows how the people were in the olden days which sometimes is a mystery.

Going into all the rooms; digging up stolen treasures and finding swords. It would be spectacular!       In conclusion, I believe that the job of an archeologist would be awesome. Although, digging isn't really my specialty, finding breathtaking artifacts and holding a little piece of history in my hands would be my dream job.

Item_Response: The Jobs of  Archaeologist   By:Kayla Truran         The jobs of Archaeologist are cool but they are hard to do.  Archaeologist first use a computer mapping software to make a image of the the area they are going to use.  Archaeologists then they look at the ground with it  and they can see things under ground.Then they mark the spot.  The spot they mark is the spot they are going to dig in.          Archaeological start digging with a skim shovels they remove thin layer of soil.  The next tool they use is picks and shovels to dig in to the earth. Item_Response: In 1994 many people were interested to study the past. The project was designed to discover the secrets of James Fort in Jamestown,Virginia. For over 200 years, People thought that fort had been washed away by a river. Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around.    The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life. Most believed that James Fort was built near the river. It was easier to dock ships there,so it made sense that the settlers choose that spot.However,objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away.The new spot probably gave the settlers more protection from enemy ships.    First objects were found in 1861. Archeologist, the name For scientists who study objects from the past, uncovered armor and weapons. They also discovered the floors of buildings.Over 100 years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built began.The National Park Service led a five year study of the area to figure out how the land was used.They knew that this would help dicide where to look for proof of the fort.

Item_Response: The job of an Archeologist is to study and uncover artifacts from the past. They use tools like a skim shovel or a trovel to remove and veiw diffrent layers of soil in order to help look for artifacts. Archeology is important because it helps see how people from our past lived and how things have changed from then to now. They find the sights where the artifacts are by looking back in history.          The tools of Arecheologist have special jobs and are needed to find artifacts. Here are the tools and their uses.   The Pick and Shovel are used to dig into the earth and get close to the  artifacts. Whisks and Dustpans are used to help clear away dirt. A Knife is used to carefully scrape dirt away from artifacts. Wheelbarrows are used to move dirt and other objects to diffrent locations. Skimshovels are shovels with flat edges and are used to carefully remove a layer of thin soil. Trowels are the last tool and are the most common tool. They are used to cut and scrape dirt so Archeologist can look at the layers.   I used this information from Source #3           Archeology helps us see into the past and learn what happened back then.In 1994 a group of people intrested in studying the past (Archeologist) started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archeological Project. It was designed to dicover the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. for 200 years people thought it had been washed away by a river but some discoveries in the area hinted it might still be around.The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life. The first objects were found in 1861.Over a hundred years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built began.Then the National Park service led a five-year study of the area.Thats when they finnaly found James Fort!The archeologists found eleven cellars, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings all within the borders of the fort.Today the group finds nearly 1 million objects each year.the objects include pottery, tools, coins, and even metal toys for children.The information learned from these objects helps us understand how the people in James Fort lived. We now know how the settlers did to fight the Powhatan tribe that often attacked them.this info was from source #1          People like George Washington leave behind history so to find what they where like before they became famous you follow that history. Archeologist thought a stone base for a farm house would be left behind . Four houses had been built on Ferry Farm land, witch is the place where George Washington lived so Archeologist had to find proof it was his so they started a dig.Records show the Washingtons had a fire in their house. The diggers found peices of burnt pottery suggesting a fire had been here. They also found part of a clay pipe. We know Washington smoked clay pipes so that is further evidence it was Washingtons house.       I got this information from source #2

Item_Response: This report will be about Archeology Tools.  Archeology is a cold hard study of old or even ancient artifacts.  It takes hard work, cautiousness, determination, and patience.  Archeology helps us understand things about people and why they made the decisions that they did.  They use all different kinds of gadgets and tools to help them find these artifacts, so that's what I'll write about first.    This paragraph will be about the tools Archeologists use to find lost artifacts.  Some of the larger tools would be the Pick and Shovel, the Wheelbarrow, and the Skim Shovel.  Some of the smaller objects include the Trowel, the Whisk and Dustpan, and the Knife.  The Knife is used to dig carefully and push dirt away from the artifacts.  The Trowel is used to do some cutting and scraping to have some sort of a view of the different layers of soil.  The Whisk and Dustpan is probably used after you find the artifact it brushes off the dirt on an artifact.  The Pick and Dustpan is used to start the dig and get down close to the object, while the skim shovel scrapes thin layers of dirt with it's flat edge and dumps it into the wheelbarrow which then takes it away from the excavation site.    In this paper I explained what Archeologists tools do and how they help them get the job done.  If there were no Archeologists, museums like the Smithsonion wouldn't exist.  Museums help us learn about History, and isn't History one of our subjects in school?  So think about it, the world needs Archeologists because we can find some pretty amazing things when we dig up the history of the people on our Earth.

Item_Response: Being an archeologist is not an easy job.  Once you are notified that there are artifacts somewhere.  You can't just start digging, or else you don't know where to dig.  First, you have to map the area with computers, then you can start digging with the skim shovels.  The skim shovels start removing layers of dirt, but be careful, you don't want to skim too far or else you might break the artifacts.  You could also start with a pick and shovel, once you are close to the artifacts.  You are very likely to use a trowel to remove the last few layers of soil. At this point, you will have to be super careful, or else you could easily break the artifacts.  If the soil surrounding the artifact is hard, you would use a knife to carefully scrape off the dirt.  If the dirt is soft or loose, you would use a whisk and dustpan.  As you can see, being an archeologist requires skill, but is still partially based on luck.  Why luck?  Well, you could be digging for 15 minutes and of found 43 treasure chests, while you could've been digging for 9 years and only found a piece of metal.  In conclusion, being an archeologist is not always easy.

Item_Response: ????An archeologist is a person who digs up objects to find more history. They use different tools, such as a: pick and shovel, whisk and dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and a trowel. They find out about the past of famous or well known people and more about their life that nobody knew about.       They find the objects or personal secrets by working as a big team. First, the team finds the place, which can track things underground, on a map using 3D computers. Then, another team starts digging in the dig. They use a type of shovel called the skim shovel that are small, flat, and sharp. They put the object found into a half-inch screen to let the dirt to fall and the object to stay. After that, they trowel to scrape and cut up the layers of the soil. Finally, the last team spend a lot of their time to study and find out more about the object and what it is. It takes a lot of time to do all this, but step by step you can get a good result.       Digging up objects and discovering things may be hard work, but you can make history out of it. People learn more and more about that person and their childhood. Being an archeologist is a big job from discovering to studying and learning about the object to making history.

Item_Response: ARCHEOLOGISTS   BY: JESSICA       An archeologist is a person who finds stuff from the past. They dig up stuff and they examine it. They find information about the stuff they dig up by examining it. They use tools to dig the stuff up. Here are some examples.   The pick and shovel. Most of the time archeologists use these tools first. They dig into the Earth to find stuff.   The whisk and dustpan. They use this to dust dirt off the artifacts and clear dirt from excavation site. So if there is a lot of dirt on something they can just brush it away.   The knife. They use this to scrape dirt away from around the artifacts.   The wheelbarrow. They use this to carry something or dirt from one place to another. So if there is a lot of dirt in one place, then they can move it to a different place. Or if there is something heavy that they need to move.   The skim shovel. A skim shovel has a flat edge so it can remove dirt carefully. So maybe there is a fragile thing in the ground. They can remove the dirt carefully.   The trowel. This is a common tool used by archeologists. They use this to cut layers of soil. Maybe they just want to view stuff but the soil is too hard.   Archeologists dug up some of George Washington's past. They have one team that focuses on digging. They have another team that focuses on mapping out the area. They use computers that track what's underground. They tell the digging people where to dig and stuff. That is all I have for this report so I guess I'm done. The End.

Item_Response: In 1994 some people that liked studying history thought that they would go to Jamestown,Virginia to try to find the James Fort that people said had been washed away for 200 years but they found some discoveries in the area that made them think it might still be there.The first item was found in 1861.A scientist who study items from the past found armor and weapons and they also discovered floors of a   building.Today the groups find nearly 1 million items each year.                                                                                                                      George Washington's home was on a Ferry Farm because of the perfect land to build a house on.Archeologists think that stone base  that was under the house is still there.So they started to dig in 2003.It took a year but they did find it.The first thing they found was the kitchen next they found was the slave quarters and storage houses.Other houses had been built on the Ferry Farm so the had to make sure it was the right house.Records show the Washington's had a fire in their house.They found burnt pieces of pottery which shows a fire was there.They also found a burnt clay pipe because Washington used to smoke them so they knew they were at the right house.                   The discovery of George Washington house is very important.The first reason is that it helps citizens know who George Washington was before he became famous.The second thing it helps is historians learn about the life Colonial Americans lived.                          Ferry Farms are open to family's.Family's can go to the summer workshops with classroom and outdoor activities.Kids can explore the site,experience how the Colonial life was and kids can become kid archeologists.They can do classes,and games and crafts.Ferry Farms are coming to life like the country's never seen before.

Item_Response: Even though and archeologist can be lots of hard work, it is still lots of fun. For example, there are lots of surprises and you don't always know what is coming next, you get to see a lot of cool things that most people don't get to see, and also kids can get involved. Plus, you don't get to say that you have seen George Washington's house very often.                 First of all, being and archeologist seems like lots of fun because there are a lot of surprises and you don't always know what is coming next. I know that I like surprises....most of the time, so maybe the job of an archeologist wouldn't be so bad. For example, it took the archeologists a lot of time to finally found James Fort. They first were seeing a lot of clues to find proof. Because you will need proof to prove to people that you found James Fort or people won't believe you, and as you may know that it takes a lot of work to find proof, most of the time. But can you imagine the great feeling that the archeologists felt when they knew for sure that they found James Fort. I know that I love the feeling of relief after a lot of hard work!                 Another great reason about being and archeologist is that you get to see a lot of cool things (artifacts) that a lot of people don't get to see, and you get to be the first. Not only do you get to see cool artifacts but you also get to use and see some cool tools. For example, when the archeologists discovered Fort James and George Washington's house, the archeologists got to discover objects that were used by people hundreds of years ago. Isn't that cool! Being and archeologist doesn't just give people excitement, but it also gives people a look at the past.                 One more reason that and archeologist seems like lots of fun is because, kids get to get involved. I may not like reading out of a textbook, but I do like doing hands on activities. It doesn't seem bad to get to go out and discover things that many people may of thought you wouldn't be able to do. Any good job takes some hard work. I thind that it would be really cool to learn about George Washington as a kid, or getting to see lots of cool artifacts! There should be a museum where kids can learn the same stuff that the archeologists discovered and doing hands on activities. Even though we wouldn't get as much fun as the archeologists did actually getting to discover, it would be lots of fun for the kids, and the archeologists would feel good about it!                 In conclusion, these were just a couple of examples of why being an archeologist is so much fun. Who knows, maybe you would want to try being an archeologist someday! Think about all the awesome things you would get to do. For instance, see cool artifacts, be the first to discover something, feel the feeling of anxiety, but then again have the feeling of relief. Like I said before, even though being an archeologist seems like lots of hard work, it is still lots of fun!

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is very very important. without archeologists we would not know so much about George Washington's childhood.        It all started in 1994 when a group were interested in studying Jamestown. They were trying to discover the secrets of James Fort. Everybody thought that the fort had been washed away by a river but the group found small remains such as armor, weapons, and floors of buildings! This was so exciting that the National Card Service led a five-year study of the James Fort area. Finally they found James Fort!        It started out as just a few marks, then they realized those marks were were the walls used to be. Then they found stone ledges built over the river. The ledges were designed to hold cannons. They also found eleven cellars, many burial sites, and ten buildings.       After that motivation the group finds over 1,000,000,000 objects each year! each object gives away more information about the James Fort and how the people inside it lived.The team still works on uncovering artifacts and learning about the James Fort.

Item_Response: The Life Of An Archeologist   By: Nick Alonzi              The life of a archeologist seems full of excitement and just searching for cool objects. It is, but it's a lot more then that. Even before the work happens it takes years to plan out the location. Then it's tiresome hours of ?finding objects in the ground on a 3D computer. Finally months of digging in the dirt for those objects. In this report you will learn the forgotten work of the archeologists.          The one of the hardest things an archeologist has to do is search out the coordinåtes of the ruins. In a article I read it took a couple years to begin the search. I once met with a professor, he told me that 'in many of my archeological digs that it took 2-3 years to come up with the location.' He said that 'it takes many calculations. We have to go off of recent reports. Sometimes we go off of findings. One time we had a huge lead when we met up with a business man who said that their is a certain place with artifacts lying around everywhere.' There also is another flaw in this work. Say your calculations are off. You could dig up an entire place for nothing. You lose a bag load of money for nothing. You now have to reconfigure your calculations and spend another 2-3 years on calculations. This is one of the many tiresome events that occur as an archeologist.          Another tiresome act that occurs is the hours of watching a screen for any sign of object in the ground. This can be as boring as staring at a wall because      There is no game, website or anything to do but watch the screen. If you are hungry or go to the bathroom you need to call someone over to take your shift. Then the other person encounters the boredom that you were experiencing. If you sit to long, your butt falls asleep. I personally hate that.    Those were 4 things that may or may not occur if you are at this post. Not only those scary life threatening events but if the fates hate you that day they will either shut down your machine or make you dig up a tin can. If you dug 15 feet into the ground for that you would be furious. This is 5-6 things that can ruin your day in at least 10 minutes.          Finally the toughest part of them all. The dig. This part is the hardest because you have to dig in the hard earth. Yes, there may be machines, but, there always won't be. Imagine breaking your back everyday. Digging and digging and digging till you find the artifact. 95% of archeologists say that they needed 30 day back therapy after the dig. Yes, back therapy. 30% also said they either needed physical therapy for a couple months or needed back surgery. Imagine that! That's why only the crazy, dedicated, and genius have a career as a archeologist. Now you may call it. The dig.          As you can see you are wrong. A job as an archeologist is a crazy career not just fun and games. If you are interested in the job and have at least two of the traits I have listed above here are the simple steps.       Get a bag load of money Take 2-3 years to plan your archeological dig. Get a huge group of crazed workers. Take hours and hours of time on a 3D computer looking for artifacts. Start to dig and dig to find the objects. Schedule a physical therapy appointment.         Now you know the basics, and always remember them, they will come in handy! See you at the dig!

Item_Response: Informational Report on a Job of a Archeologist                                                             By: Brianna Geiger               Have you heard of an archeologist?  Have you ever been an archeologist?  What is an archeologist?  What do they do?  All of those questions might be going through your head right now, but I will answer all those questions.  Anyways, to be an archeologist is a lot of work.  Also they have to take a lot of classes to know what to do .  The good thing is that they can get a lot of money for selling all their precious artifacts to dealers.  Therefore, the job of an archeologist can be very complicated.               First of all, to be an archeologist is a lot of work.  You have to work all day long, which can be very tiring.  Also to be an archeologist can be very slow because you have to dig up artifacts that are very precious.  Sometimes you have to use paintbrushes, small shovels (skim shovels), and wooden picks, this is called troweling.  Even if you have a big group digging to find artifacts, it can take over two weeks to find and dig up something.  Furthermore, archeologists have a lot of work.               Secondly, to be an archeologist you have to take lots of classes.  For example, you have to learn about history to know where and what happened in the past.  They do this to know where to dig and what to dig/look for.  You also have to take archeology to learn how to dig and to dig properly.  There is also a lot more classes you have to take to be an archeologist, but that would take a while.  Lastly, you have to take a lot of classes to be an archeologist.               After all, you can get lots of money if you sell the artifacts to a dealer.  This is the good thing about being an archeologist-you get a lot of money out of it.  If you sell the artifacts to a dealer, they can give you lots of money for the artifact(s).  If the artifact(s) are very old you can get a lot of money for it.  If the artifact(s) are not really really old you will get less money, but still a lot of money.  All in all, this is the good part about being an archeologist- you get a lot money.               To sum it up, to be an archeologist is very complicated.  Archeologists get a lot of money.  You have to take a lot of classes to be one.  The on thing that is good is the money that you get.  Well, I hope you learned something new about the job of an archeologist.

Item_Response: Archeologists                                                                             By Rachael Baker       Archeologists have amazing jobs, like paleontologists they dig in the Earth, but what, makes archeologists so special is they dig up artifacts that help us learn about the past. In this essay you'll learn about Jamestown Isand, working at young George Washington's house and you will also learn a little more about the tools they use and how they use them. I hop you learn more about archeologists by reading this essay.               First I'll tell you a little about Jamestown Island. In 1994 a group of people started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. They wanted to rediscover Fort James in Virginia. For more than 200 years people believed that Fort James had been carried away by a rushing river, but now there starting to doubt that theory. The was believed to be built either by a river or father away to be protected from enemies. The first artifacts were found in 1861. Archeologists found armor, weapons, floors and even ceilings of the fort. Now people are trying to find the exact place the fort was at. There was a five year study that gave them many important clues. Then they found it imagine how happy you would be! Today people can find a million objects or artifacts each year. They find pottery, glass and many other artifacts.Wow archeologists have to work really hard to find the sites even before they dig.       Next we will talk about George Washington's old house. George lived at a place called ferry farm. Finding the spot was very difficult because the farm was very big. but they made an estimate and started digging they soon found the stone base of the house.  Since other houses had been built there they needed proof it was young George's house. Records say the house burned down and they found burnt pottery. They also found clay pipes which they know Washington loved to smoke them. The archeologists have to be very careful while digging and handling artifacts. One wrong move and an important part of our history could be destroyed in seconds. Up to 35 people could be working on one site. They also use Highly advanced computers. They even let kids help out!       Finally I'll tell you about tools they are the pick and shovel used to dig the earth close to objects, whisk and dustpan used to dust the dirt off artifacts, knife used for careful digging near the artifact, Wheelbarrow is used to move artifacts or dirt away from the dig site, skim shovel used to remove a thin layer of soil and finally the trowel used to scrape, cut or view the soil differently. Wow that a lot of tools to dig right and ensure the safety of every artifact.       To sum it up Archeologists are amazing people who help us understand our history by literally digging it up. They have uncover Fort James and young George Washington's house. They use special tools and have to be extra careful. I hope now you have learned a lot more about archeologists. Maybe you want to be one too.

Item_Response: Finding James Fort                                      By:Dylan Foss   An archeologist has to work very hard for their job because first of all they take all of this time searching for things in the history of the United States of America.All archeologists have different jobs like some people use computer and some use tool to like dig up things that are a big part of history.   The archeologists found many things such as tools,pottery,coins and metal toys when that kids used to play with.They found these things when they were searching for James Fort.The archeologists also found eleven cellars, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings all within the border of the site.Today, the group fins nearly one million objects a year. In the 1600s people used to throw away their trash down an unused well or into a big pit,While digging in the area , the archeologists found the trash the settlers threw away, including bones from animals that they ate.The information learned from these objects helps the archeologists understand how the people lived in the James Fort.That is the end of that summary.                                                            Digging up Georges Past                                                                            By:Dylan Foss                                           Recent discoveries at Washington's childhood home has helped historians know more about Washington as a boy.People have lived on the land known as Ferry Farm for over 12,000 years.The process of archeologist digging at the Ferry Farm is a careful one. The tools used by archeologists are a Pick and Shovel.Most digs start with the pick and shovel and are used to dig into the earth close to the artifacts.The whisk and dust pan are used to brush dirt off artifact and clear away dirt from the excavation site.The knife is used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts.Another tool that is used is a wheelbarrow and that is used to move things from one place to another.One other tool is a skim shovel that is used to carefully remove a thin layer off the artifact.The last tool is the trowel and is used to scrape things. The ferry farm offers many opportunities for kids to get involved.The George Washington society runs summer workshops with both classroom and outdoor activities.Kids can explore the site even.This challenges kids to solve puzzles about the work being done at ferry farm.That is the end of that summary.

Item_Response: The search for history is a never ending road, in this essay I will be writing about Fort James in Virginia. The fort was built around the start of the 16th century to protect a river entering the mainland of the new land that had been claimed. The teams found many amazing things like pottery, tools, and coins. They also found trash, like the bones of animals that the colonists had eaten. That investigation also gave us more information about the attack of the Powhatan tribe. It also told us of how they built things back in those times like, all the cellers, burial sites, and the foundatoins of 10 buildings inside the boundries of the fort.

Item_Response: An archeologist has an important and very hard job. They find many artifacts. They have specific ways to do their digs. They also have many special tools they use for their digs. Archeologist find many cool artifacts. Artifacts are anything that was made or used in the past. They do their digs at various places that were important in the past. It might be at James Fort, George Washington's house, or maybe they are looking for dinosaur fossils.                      Archeologist are separated into three teams with up to 35 people. The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground. This information is used to get a look of what the area looks like before team two starts digging. Team two is the team that does the digging and gets the artifacts out of the ground. The archeologist start the dig with a skim shovel. This shovel is flat, small, and sharp. This makes it so it can remove different, thin layers of soil one at a time. Then they place it in a box with a half inch screen at the bottom, so dirt can fall out with the artifact still in. They also use other tolls besides for the skim shovel, like the trowel, pick and shovel, wheelbarrow, and more.              Archeologist jobs take a long time to do. If an archeologist rushed his or her work at the dig than they could brake very valuable objects that help us figure out the story of the past, history. The National Park Service led a five-year study to figure out how the land on which Fort James was on, was used. Five years is a long time, but it is worth it to archeologist who do the work. To plot the land, carefully dig for artifact, and to identify what they are takes a long time.              Now you know why they archeologist dig, to find artifacts. You also know how they dig, in three teams with up to 35 people. Another thing you know is what they dig with, many different tools. If I had the job of an archeologist, I would either want to be the team at the dig or the archeologist who plot the dig on their computers. I would want to be a person at the dig because I like using pick, and I want to try to use a skim shovel. I would also want to be one of the people plotting the dig out because it sounds fun using the 3D computers. No matter how much fun it is, being an archeologist is a tough job.

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist           The job of an archeologist is to dig for artifacts from the past. With the items they find we can learn more about are past and important events and people in history. Archeologists use many tool to help them with their work. If we didn't have archeologists much of what we know today we would not.              Two big archeological findings were the discovery of James Fort and of George Washington's childhood home. In 1994 James Fort was discovered in Jamestown, Virginia. First they found marks in the ground then they realized it must have been bigger then they thought. Now they find nearly 1 million objects a year from James Fort. They found George Washington's childhood home in 2003. First they found some smaller buildings. Then the main structure. They found pipes and burnt pottery that supported their thoughts that the house had suffered a fire. Now they have activities there to educate people on the house's history. Thanks to these discoveries we know more about history.            Now you have learned about two important digs you need to learn about the tools they use. They use a pick and shovel to dig close to artifacts, so they won't be damaged. They use a whisk to clear of artifacts and a knife to remove dirt from them. They use a wheelbarrow and a thin shovel for careful work. They use alot of tools and each one has a certain job.           Over all being an archeologist is hard work, but there are people who go out there and help us understand history. Now we have learned alot from them.

Item_Response: We are going to talk about archaeology. We are going to learn about some different things.      Lets start with Fort James. Archaeologist found the first artifacts from Fort James in 1861. They found armor and weapons. They also discovered the floors of Fort James. A 100 years later people started trying to find the exact spot where the fort was built.They first thing that the archaeologist found was marks on the ground that showed where the walls used to be. The archaeologist heard stories and made drawings that lead them to relize that the fort was triangle shaped. They discovered that the fort stretched all the way to the river. At the river they foundledges that were designed to hold cannons.They also found 11cellars, many burial sites and 10 building all inside the fort. Today archaeologist fing almost 1,000,000 objects each year. In the area archaeologist found the trash that the settlers threw away. Some of the things found were animal bones of the animals that they ate. The archaeologist found many objects that were used everyday hundreds of years ago.      Next we are going to talk about the George Washington house. Archaeologist started digging in 2003. It took them over a year but they had found the kitchen, slave quaters, and storage houses. They did not find the main farm house untill a few years later.      Lets talk about just archaeology now. First there are 3 teams. 1 team can consist of 35 people. The first group makes a map on 3D computers. The maps help the people who actually dig know where they are going and how deep they are going to dig. The  second team is the team who digs up the artifacts. The third team is the people who later study the artifacts in a lab. Some of the tools that archaeologist use are pick and shovel, whisk and dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and trowel. Each one of the tools does something different.       Now you know a little bit about archeaology and what archeologist do.

Item_Response: Archeologists              Have you ever wondered what you wanted to be when you grow up? Or what job you may want to do? Well today I am going to tell you all about what an archeologist does for a living, and how they do it.            Archeoloy is the study of fossils and old arifacts. An archeologist is a person who studies fossils and old artifacts. In other words, archeology is just the study of old objects that were dug up and dusted off.            First, they find something that they may be interesed in finding more about, like dinosaurs. They sudy them and read all sorts of books about them and learn the different names and bones. They have to make sure they know almost everything about that topic. To be able o dig up these creatures they have to do a lot of researching. The research what they ate, what they looked like, their bones, where they lived, and so on.They had to know all of this because when it came time to dig they had to know which animal, and where to find it.              The next step is getting together the right tools, and finding out where to dig. Once again they have research about where to find hey animal(s) and what tools to use. You dont want to show up to the digging spot with only a shovel and a wheelbarrow. They need to bring a pick and a shovel,to start your dig. A whisk and a dustpan, for brushing off he artifacts, and a knife for scraping dirt from around the artifacts. They also need a skim shovel,  trowel, and a wheelbarrow. To find the right spot is the hardest. You have to research where they lived and may have died.            Lastly, the archeologist goes to the sight, finds where to dig with a computor, and starts digging. When they find something they usually dig carefully around it, then dust it off. When they have made a discovery they may sell it, or give it to a museum.               In conclusion archeology is a very hard job, and being an archeologists is very hard, and important too. This report may make this job sound easy, but it is actually the opposite. It is a challenge and some archeologists don't find many things. If ou like challenges and hard work this might just be the job for you! If you hinks it's just cool and want to see some fossils, go to a museum and look at all he shells and fossils they have. Some museums actually have a sound proof, glass room where you can see reakl archeologists dustin and cleaning some fossils! Here's what I want you to do, try some activities, have our parents bury some oys in a sand box and have you find them. It migh actually be more fun than its sounds to you!

Item_Response: Archeologists         Archeologists  study objects that have been used by historical figures many many years ago. Most of the time archeologists study from 5-10 years or more on a site, such as the one they studied about George Washington. They started digging in 2003, and over a year later, they found up to three rooms. They were the kitchen, the slave quarters, and storage houses. They had heard that there was a fire that happened in the Washington house, and they needed proof that this plantation was actually Geaorge Washinton's house. After lots of digging, the archeologists found burnt pottery, and parts of a clay pipe. Since George Washington smoked clay pipes, it was now obvious that this plantation had belonged to the Washingtons.      Usually on digging sites, there are a big number of teams/groups. There can be up to 35 people on a team!  Archeologists use up to six sets of tools. They are the Pick and Shovel, which most digs start with these tools, used to dig in the earth close to the artifacts. Second there's the Whisk and Dustpan, used to brush the dirt off the artifacts and items gently. Third there's the knife, used for careful digging and used to get the dirt out from hard to reach places. Fourth there's the Wheelbarrow, used to move objects and artifacts away from the site or to carry dirt out of the site. Fifth, there's thw Skim Shovel, which is a shovel with a flat surface used to ccarefully remove thin layers of dirt and/or soil with each scoop. Finally there's the Trowel, which is probably the most common tool used by archeologists, used to scrape and cut to view different layers of soil. And that is what archeologists do.

Item_Response: Archeologists have been very helpful to us, digging up the the past and doing things that we never even dreamed of. Archeologists are very important people and if you want to help 'dig up the past' and work hard digging into the ground I would suggest being an archeologist for your future job.       Archeologists in in Jamestown in 1994 were trying to discover the secrets of their James Fort in Virginia. Everyone thought it had been washed away by a river but maybe some new discoveries may be made.The fort was built in 1607. The first objects were found in 1861 uncovered armors, weapons, and floors of a building.  The National Park Service led a five-year study of the land. Thats when they finally found James Fort! They first found marks of where the walls used to be, and they found stories and drawings that made the archrologists know that it was shaped like a triangle. Today they find nearly 1 million objects each year that includes pottery tools, or coins. It is very exciting to discover new things that were used hundreds of years ago.      Have you ever heard of Ferry Farm? A lot of people jave lived there but archeologists just found out that George Washington used to live there! When the archeologists dug up there they found a lot of things that George Washington used. They split up into groups, one digging, one getting the objects out of the dirt, and another trying to find out what the artifacts are. The dicovery of Washington's home is very important because you can understand who George washington was, the desisions he made, and the life that he lived. Maybe you can help dig up George Washington's artifacts when you grow up.       Archeologists need tools to 'dig up the past'. The most important tools are the pick and shovel because they dig up the dirt so that you can find the artifacts. They also use a whisk and dustpan to brush dirt off the artifact and clear away dirt. Archeologists use knives to scape dirt away from around the artifact, and a wheelbarrow to carry dirt away so that they can dig more. Some extra tools are a skim shovel and a trowel to remove dirt. The archeologists need a lot of tools to do their work so if you like tools an archeologist would be a good job for you.      All in all an archeologist is a very helpful and interesting job.  If you like finding cool things, using tools and getting dirty, an archeologist is a good job for you. I hope that after you read this you will think of being an archeologist as your future job!

Item_Response: Fort James and George Washington are very important people and event to us. They are very historical and breathtaking. They are important for many reasons because George Washington took part during the American Revolutionary War and Fort James was in Jamestown,Virginia where it was one of the first settlements in North America for England.                      George Washingtons father, Augustine Washington, moved his family to Ferry Farm at the age of 6. Archeologists believed that the stone base under George Washingtons house is still there. It can take up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section!The discovery of Washingtons home is important. First, it gives the citizens of the U.S. a better perspective of Washington and his family before and after he became famous. Another, because it tells of a life of a Colonial American and how they lived.Clearly, the dicovery of his past is quite important.                     Fort James was built around 1607. When settlers had arrived there they thought that it was near water. So it was easier to dock ships there. The new spot gave the settlers more protection from enemy ships. Fort James was located at Jamestown, Virginia. For over 200 years people had thought that it was washed away.In 1994, a group of people became intrested in this fort and started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. The very first object that they had found was in 1861. When they had first discovered James Fort they had found a set of marks on the ground.Its swampy low lands made them leave and find a better settlement to make crops. Clearly, its was a good and bad place to settle in.                All in all, it is exciting to dicover objects that were regularly used by people who lived hundreds of years ago. And it gives us a piece of knowledge and information about are past and ties us to the people who firsted started the American Colonies.Into what is know today The United States of America.

Item_Response: Archaeologists                                                                              What is an archaeologist? An archaeologist is a person who studies the artifactsof long ago. They use facts from the artifacts to solve long ago mysteries.\              They helped solve the mysteries of James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia and solved the mysteries of George Washington's childhood. These people use specific tools to solve the mysteries. Some examples of tools are the pick, shovel, whisk and dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and a trowel. Before the archaeologists start digging, they use 3D computer models to see what is underground carefully. Then, the archaeologists can start digging. First, the   archaeologists must use the tools very carefully to find any antiques that are very small. They use big sifters to carefully observe the small antiques. Once they find treasues that proves what happened long ago, they will have solved the mystery on what they wanted to solve.                 They just don't dig just like that. They must dig very, very carefully. It can even take two weeks to dig and sift through a 25-square-foot-section. They use common sense and other things to prove about the world.

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist             To be an Archeologist you have to have excelent grades in school,  because an Archeologist is a job that people had all A+'s on their report card!  Now let's get to the good part of this report,  An Archeologist is a person who finds fossils of animals who lived long ago,  like a Dinosoar,  or a Woley Mamath!  Or just a regular animal that we know today.  Archeologist's sometimes go to the desert, or moutains, and other places they go to find fossils!             The tools that Archeologists use is, a pick and shovel, that most digs start with these two tools.  Used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts.  A whisk and dustpan, used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site.  A knife, used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts.  A wheelbarrow, used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away from the excavation site.  A skim shovel, a shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layor of soil with each scoop.  And a trowel, this is probably the most common tool in archeology.  Used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.  These tools help Archeologists in many many different ways!             And this is the job of an Archeologist, and what they do, and what tools they use for the finding of fossils and scraps of any thing or animal that is left behind.  And remember if you want to become this amazing person make sure that you do an excelent job and school, keep up the good work, and never give up your dreams to be an Archeologist!

Item_Response: Acheologists               Acheologists are a special kind of scientist that goes back into the past and digs up old things that they think might help them learn about famous people and things that lived long ago.They started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archeological Project in 1994. For a long time people thought that the fort in Jamestown was washed away from the waves. They aso thought that it was really close to the shore.               The first object found in Jamestown was in 1861. The National Park Sevice led a five year group to scout the areafor all different kinds of things that went from weapons to potary to bricks. Then they finally found Jamestown with the help of maping computers.Today groups of up to thirty-five people find almost a million pieces of infomation each year.            Archeologists use these things to help them with their work.       Pick and Shovel    Used to start the digging at their digging site.       Whisk and Dustpan   Used to brush all the dirt on the artifacts off the artifacts.       Wheelbarrow   Used to move different items from one place to the other place easier.       Skim Shovel   This shovel is used for gently taking little layers of soil off at a time.       Trowel   This is used to scrape andcut into the soil so the archeologists can get a good view of whats under the soil.             It is easier for the archeologiss to find more hidden things than it was when they first started because they have a lot more things that are high tect right now. It still takes a long time to find all of the artifacts but it's faster than it was when they first started.
