Item_Response: Digging for History              Do you ever wonder what job is the job which requires you to dig up history? Recently, I read some articles about archeology and how it is used to understand history. The process of digging up objects is long and quite confusing. The steps include digging up objects, cleaning them off, and identifying them. These all need extreme care.              While digging up things, archeologist use pickaxes and shovels to dig up top layers of dirt and stone. The dirt archeologists dig up are transported elsewhere using a wheelbarrow. Another digging tool is the trowel, which is used to scrape and cut different layers of dirt. It is very common. These tools, except for the wheel barrow, are used to dig up artifacts. Artifacts are the objects from a long time ago, that tell us about our past.              After, the archeologists dig up artifacts, the clean them off. The tools they use are the knife and the whisk. The knife is used to scrape off the dirt on an artifact. The whisk is used to brush the dirt off. When using the knife, archeologists must use extreme care so they won't hurt the artifact.              Lastly, archeologists must identify the object to know about their past. There are laboratories for identifying objects. For example, if there is pottery made with a type of clay inaccessible in our part of the world, we could know trading routes for Native Americans. Bones of animals could tell us what type of meat our people ate. In George Washington's house, there were many things. Most of those things could be used to tell about Washington's past.                  In conclusion, an archeologist's work is very confusing. They need to dig up, clean, and identify these artifacts. Although their work is tough, it's worth it to go through it. We learn about our past and what happens in it.

Item_Response: Finding Fort James                  The archaeologists wanted to discover the secrets of James Fort. In, 1994 a group of people called the ''Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeologist Project'' wanted to know about the secrets of James Fort. They designed to discover the secrets of  James Fort. Over 200 years, legend says that peole thought the fort was washed away by a river. Some say that peole still think the fort is underground. In conclusion, the archaeologists wanted to find out the secrets of Fort James.             The fort was built in 1607. Settlers came from England to start a new life. People would built ships, start businesses, and built new homes. They would even grow crops like corn, tabacco, and other crops. It was easier to dock ships there, and settlers choose the spot there. Settlers also started alot of businesses. The spot even gave people the protection from enemy ships. In conclusion, the settlers came from England to James Fort to start a new life.                 The objects were founded located further away from the fort. The achaeologists found the first objects in 1861. They study the objects that uncovered that armor and weapons in James Fort. They discovered it was under the floors of the buildings. The armor and the weapons were used to protect the fort from enemies, who tried to attack the fort. Maybe, the settlers put the armor and the weapons under the floor of the building so no one will still them. Plus, the enemies won't know where they hid the armor and the weapons. In conclusion, they found armor and weapons under the buildings of James Fort.                  Over 100 years, the group found the exact spot where the fort was built. The National Park Service had a five-year study. They were figuring it out how the land was used by the settlers. They need the proof so that it will help them to decide where they would find James Fort. They have been studying using computer mapping software to make the image for the area. Also there using maps and probably to scan the armor and weapons to find  James Fort. In conclusion, they need the proof to find James Fort.                   That's when they found James Fort! The first thing they have to do is find a set of marks on the ground. The second thing, to do is the marks showed where the fort's walls used to be. All the stories peole heard that drawings they made, the archaeologists knew that James fort formed like a triangle. They believed that the settlers used the stone ledges to built over the river. Plus, the designs on the ledges were canons. The most amazing part is, that the archaeologist found eleven cellars, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings all with the border of the fort.                   In conclusion, today the group found nearly 1 million objects each year. The objects include pottery, tools, coins, and metal toys for children. Plus, in the 1600s, people used to throw their trash in a unused well or into a big pit. All their scarps were there, including the bones of animals they ate.The objects help us learn more information in history and about how the settlers in James Fort lived.

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is a very interesting job.  You have to plan the digs very carefully and make sure everything is in perfect order.  There are three main groups in archeology with up to thirty-five people in each.        The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground.  That information is recorded so that the diggers know what is underground before people started digging.  This was very helpful to the discovery of Fort James.  The archeologists needed a good map of the area, so they used the computer mapping software.  The 3D computers are a very helpful tool when looking for the spot where archeologists want to start digging.        The second team focuses on the actual digging.  The site where diggers dig is called a dig. Those archeologists start digging with a tool called a skim shovel.  A skim shovel has a flat edge and with each scoop removes a thin layer of soil.  When archeologists dug up some artifacts from George Washington's childhood, the first tools they used were skim shovels.  The second tools they used were shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks.        The third and last team works in the lab.  They study the objects that were found.  They have to work very carefully so none of the artifacts would get broken.        I hope you have learned about archeologists and what they do!

A trowel is used to scrape or cut layers to see the different layers.                           Archeologists also use a 3D computer to track find artifacts or to see what is underground. Item_Response: An Archeologist's Job                                    You make think an archeologist is just someone who digs up stuff, but that is not true. An archeologist is someone who uses artifacts to study the past. Archeologists have a hard job to do.                     Archeologists have to be organized, careful, and use their time wisely to get their job done. It can take long times to complete a dig. First, a team will map the area using special devices so that they can see what is underground. This helps the people know what the area they are digging in looked like before they started digging. Then another team starts the actual digging. They start the dig with a special shovels which are very small, flat, and sharp. With these shovels they remove only small layers of dirt. Once they have that soil, they will put it in a box where the dirt will fall out while the artifacts stay in. Another thing they may do is troweling which is done with paint brushes, small shovels, and wooden picks. It can take two weeks to remove a twenty-five-square-foot area with troweling. Finally, a different team will study the things they found. It is a very slow process.                      Archeologists use many different tools. They will use a pick and shovel to dig down into the Earth. A whisk and dustpan are used to tidy up the artifacts or clear dirt from the dig-site. Also they will use a knife for careful digging and scrapping dirt of the artifacts found. A wheelbarrow is used to transport dirt or the artifacts to another place. Taking a thin layer of dirt is the skim shovel's job. A very common tool, the trowel, is used to scrape and cut so you can see the different layers of soil. Those are common tools used be archeologists.                      Archeologists have found artifacts in many different places. George Washington's house is one. They have found things there that have helped them learn new things about George Washington's life. It also helps us know about him before he became famous. Another place is James Fort. We now know about the settler's every day life and challenges.                      Archeologists are actually very important. They help us know what we know about history. They are more than just diggers.

Item_Response: This report will be about the profession of archaeology. Archaeology has a lot to give to history. It is the digging and looking for objects that have been buried over time.You will learn about two digs in particular. The James Fort dig and the George Washington childhood dig.                    This paragraph is about the James Fort dig. The first objects that were found were dug up in 1861. They uncovered weapons, and armor. After a 5 year study they found James Fort. the first thing they found were markings on the ground where the walls used to stand. Then they found ledges built over the river to hold cannons. they also found eleven cellars, and dozens of burial sites.                      This next part of the report is about  a George Washington Childhood dig. They found burnt clay pottery that suggested that there was a fire. They also found a part of clay pottery. They new that Washington smoked clay pipes, so that suggests  that Washington lived there. It took them two weeks to dig a 25 square-foot section of land.                       The archaeologists use a variation of tools to uncover artifacts. They use picks and shovels. These tools are used to start the dig by breaking into the dirt. They use a whisk and dustpan to brush dirt off of the artifacts. A knife is used for careful digging. They use a wheel barrow to move dirt and artifacts from one place to the next. They use a skim shovel to carefully remove a thin layer of dirt away from the dig. They also use a trowel to scrap and cut to see different layers of soil.                           Archaeology has a lot to do with the uncovering of our history. It is important to keep organizing archaeological digs. We need to keep leaning about our history. Also we need to keep teaching about what was discovered on archaeological digs.

Item_Response: DIGGING UP THE PAST                 HOW DO ARCHEOLOGISTS FIND ALL OF THESE THINGS THAT WERE IN WASHINGTON'S HOUSE ALL THOSE YEARS AGO? THE PROCESS OF DIGGING AT THE FERRY FARM IS A CAREFUL ONE. EACH YEAR, MANY TEAMS WILL WORK ON THE SITE. THERE CAN BE UP TO 35 PEOPLE ON A TEAM! THE FIST TEAM MAPS THE AREA USING THE 3D COMPUTERS THAT CAN TRACK WHAT IS UNDERGROUND. THE INFORMATION IS THERE SO PEOPLE WILL KNOW WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE. OTHER PEOPLE START TO DIG SO THEY CAN FIND STUFF TO.                                                THEY START TO DIG WITH A SKIM SHOVEL. YOU PROBPLY DON'T KNOW WAHT THAT IS. Item_Response: Archeology                                    Aidan 5/20/13              Archeology is the finding and study of historic artifacts. Archeology can be used to find out about historic peoples' lives. It can also be used to find out where someone or something is. Archeology can be a tough process. There are three main parts to it, determining who you want to learn about, finding the artifacts, and studying them.          Step 1, determing who you want to find out about, is probably the easiest part. You can learn about George Washington, Martin Luther King, or maybe Rosa Parks. You can look on a computer to research who you want to learn about, which might tell you a little bit about what you might find. If you dont have a computer, use a book. Then you can get on to the next step.          Step 2, digging, is the most tiresome part of the job. Most archeologists use a skim shovel to start. A skim shovel is a flat shovel that digs small layers of dirt at a time. Then they put the dirt in a wheel barrow to be examined. They then trowel through it with a trowel, or a pitch fork and make sure they didn't mis anything. Now to study!          Step 3, studying, will be the part all archeologists want: finding out about the artifacts. From your research, you might have discovered that your person likes to farm. If you found a hoe or a bucket, that might prove it. If you find a lot of tools, you might find out that they were a carpenter. If you are lucky your discovories will be important. Even if not, it still will be good to know that you tried! Maybe you will be the one to discover more about George Washington's childhood!          Archeology is one of the best things to study history. It is good exersize, and could reward you. Studying under a microscope, or digging could be great fun! Most things in museums is found by archeology. digging and studying can find many things!

Item_Response: The work of archeology is a very dangerous job. It takes lots of determination and hard work.   Archeology is the study of earth, or ground. Archeologists find many interesting artifacts such as; dinosaur bones, teeth, and sometimes claws! However not everything an archeologist does is look for dinosaur fossils, they can also look for presedential items from the past! They can also look for lost cities,towns,or even colonies.   Keep reading!                                                                                                                                                                                    Archeologists need many tools to actually BE an archeoligist here they are:   A pickaxe and shovel A whisk and dustpan A knife A Wheelbarrow A Skim Shovel A Trowel        A pickaxe is used to break through stone,and a shovel is used to dig through dirt. These two materials are used to start out the search.        A whisk and dustpan are used to clear dirt off the artifact without harming the artifact.        A knife is used dig around artfacts and to scrape dirt off the artifact carefully.        Wheelbarrows are used to move items to one place to another carefully.   One skim shovel is used to scoop a very thin layer of dirt.   When you see someone use a trowel, this means they are trying to view the diffrent layers of dirt.            Now you know what archeoligists search for and what tools they need. Hopefully someday one of these reader's will become an archeoligists!

Item_Response: The job of archeologist is hard.  Being and archeologist is cool but, you learn things from doing things.  Archeologists look for thing in the past.  For example,the dinosaurs.  The archeologists have been studying dinosaur fossils for a long time.  In the museum there dinosaur fossils that make a dinosaur.  Archeologists find the fossils then they turn them in to scientists to see what bone it belongs to then they build it.                                             Archeologists spend there time finding things from the past.  So they try to find things in history from dinosaurs-now.  Archeologists went to Ferry Farm to see George Washington's house.  Only the base of the house was there.  None of the archeologists new were the Washington house was at.  They started digging in 2003.  The archeologists found the kitchen,slave quarters,and storage houses.The archeologists found the farmhouse a few years later.  The archeologists were digging more to make sure that the house was George Washington's house.                   Archeologists found burnt pottery.  So the archeologists occur that there was a fire in the house.The archeologist knew George Washington smoked clay pipes.  So they gives more proof that it is the right house.  Each year many archeologists get put into teams.  The team have up to 35 people on there team.  The first team maps he area using 3D computers to see what is underground.  The other team focuses on were there digging.  The team uses skim shovels,shovels are small, flat and sharp shovels.Soil is placed in a box with half inch screen at the bottom.  This lets the the dirt fall out and the artifacts stay in.The diggers also use troweling.  It takes up to 2 weeks for the diggers to dig a 25-square-foot section.

Item_Response: Archeologist are hard workers. What do they do exactly. Well archeologist do many things for science, education, curiousity, and even just for our amusement. There are plenty of resons for being an archeoligist. Their work is not easy at alL. Read more to find out what exactly an acheroligist does, why, and the tools they use!                                                         WHAT THEY DO       An acheologist is the kind of scientist who likes to 'dig' depper.   They discover artifacts of all kinds from tall caves, to deep oceans. Artifacts are objects from the past. Archeologist ue the artifacts to discover many things from our history. Such as, Gorge Washingtons old house, The exact spot were for jams was built, why the Titanic sank, and more! You might see all kinds of artifacts in local musems. Usually archeologist dig in  the ground or in ccaves to find what their searching for                                WHY ARCHEOLOGIST ARE IMPORTANT       Archeologist find artifacts that ckuld even answer some of the biggest questions of the wrold today. The artifacts they find gives us a little piece of what it was like for people, and any living thing a long time ago. Our children, and ourselves will be able to learn about htese artifacts and what it was like back then. Sometimes they find extinct animal bones or carcasses (if frozen in glaciers) from about 1,000,000+ years ago! Such as the Tyranasaurus, Saber Toothed tiger, Wooly Mammoth, Megalodon, and more. Its also good to know how the creatures of our world 'Evolved'. It gives us some ideas of what the animals of today might be capable of.                                             THE DANGERS THEY FACE        While at work, archeologist face many dangers no matter what terain their in. Some have even died from sickness, or injuries. Lets say your an archeologist on a mountain, digging ino its depths. its possible an avalanche could occur, you fall off, or an animal attacks you. Some tools are hazerdous has well. Such as the knife. We all know what would happen if somebodey accidentaly cut themselves. Some archeologist go on several year long journies to remote places. They might encounter an unknown disease that is uncureable.                                                           TOOLS USED        Arheologist use a number of tools for many reasons. here is a list of too,ls and why they use them.   Pick and Shovel: to usualy dig through dirt or rocks   Whisk and dustpan: To gently clear off dust from artifacts   Knife: Used for CAREFUL digging and for scraping off dirt from hard to reach places on an artifact.   Wheelebarrow: Used to move a number of items, or a big object from one place to another, or to move dirt/soil away from an excavation site   Skim shovel: A shovel with a square-like shape used to remove thin layers of soil with each scoop   Trowel: Used to scrabe away diffrent layers of soil.   These are just a small number of the most simple tools used for archeolagy. You might even own few of these tools.                                                      CONCLUSION       Its true that archeologist have a very tough job. They provide us with alot of knowlage of our history, and other facinating things from long ago. Next time you go to a musem amd see an old artifact, youll know who worked hard to find it. Archeologist face many dangers to find the objects, and usually have no success. Go to your local musem to learn more about archeologist and their jobs!

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is to find historical objcts of the past. Archeologists uncover historical figures that give us clues about America`s history.       Archeologists have studied many different thing. They`ve studied Fort James and George Washington`s home on Ferry Farm land. Theyhave discovered many other things too.       While discovering Fort James archeologists also found the places where colonists would dump their trash. Colonists would dump their trash in unused wells or garbage pits.       When discovering George Washibngton`s house they found burnt poetry and many other things. They first found the kitchen, slave quaters, and storage houses.       At lesast 4 houses have been built on Ferry Farm land. So, archeologists had to find the right house. They also had to have proof that the house they thought was George Washingtons was his house.       Archeologists use many different tools. These tools are: pick and shovel, whisk and dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and trowel. A pick and shovel are used to dig into the earth, close to artifacts. Whisk and dustpan are used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site. A knife is used for careful digging and to scraope dirt from around the artifacts. Wheelbarrows are used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away from the excavation site. Skim Shovel is used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop. Trowels are used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.

Item_Response: ?Archeology      ??By Elizabeth Starkey         Have you ever wondered what it would be like to be an archeologist or what tools they used? Or how we can learn from archeologists? Well, it is very interesting to be an archeologist, in my opinion, and it is very hard!         It's interesting and boring because of the things you might find. Some people have found remains of historical artifacts like walls of Fort James or broken pottery from George Washington's house. You could also find clothes and other things that people used back then. Who knows what you could find out there? Only time will tell! It could also be boring when you don't find anything for a while. You could dig up a large area of dirt and not find anything.         Archeologists used many types of tools for many different reasons. One tool that archeologists use most often is the 'whisk and dustpan.' These are used like a dustpan at home! You would use the whisk to clear off the dirt on the artifact. Then, the dirt would go into the dustpan. Picks and shovels are often used to start the search. They use the pick to chip away at the dirt. The shovel is used to move the dirt out of the area (most likely into the wheelbarrow). The knife is used for carefully scraping dirt off of the artifact. The wheelbarrow is just used for a simple transport of dirt to somewhere else; most likely away from the digging site. A skim shovel would be used for removing a thin layer of dirt from the earth. The most often tool on a digging site would be a trowel. This is just a smaller version of a shovel used for digging and to show the different layers of dirt.         If you have ever wondered what we could learn from archeology? Time to put that question to rest! We can learn a lot from archeologists! One example would be that we could find out what colonial life was like. Archeologists found George Washington's house that he lived in when he was a boy. They found burnt, broken pottery, which indicated that there was once a fire at George Washington's house. We have also found some remains of Fort James. Archeologists started digging up armor and weapons that would indicate that Fort James was built in that area. We can also see what it was like to live in Fort James, like several cellars, burial grounds, and toys for children, all in the same area.         As you can see, we could learn a lot from archeology and fro the people who dedicate their time to helpus learn about colonial life.

Item_Response: An archeologist has a special and important job. They have to plan out what they are trying to find, carefully and slowly follow the directions, and do research. Even when this tiring process is done, all your work will pay off.                   When archeologists want to find out more about something in the past, they get a team for the digging process and finding information. For them to find more about the past they have to do research on it just like the people did when they found Fort James. They have to know where the historical place was, what are they trying to find, and what happened to the historical place to start digging or looking for clues.                   When archeologists are ready and they have done there research, they look for clues to see where the historical place is.When archeologists were finding Fort james, the National Park Serice led a five-year study of the area to figure out how the land was used. They used that information so they could know where to look for proof of the fort. That's what archeologist have to do to map out where the historical place is.                   When the archeologists find the historical place, they get their tools ready to dig. there are alot of tools they use on the site. Most archeologist start digging with a pick and shovel. They use it to dig in to the earth, close to the artifacts. Other main tools they use are whisk and dustpan ( to brush dirt off of the artifacts), knife ( used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifact), wheelbarrow ( used to move items from one place to another), skim shovel ( a shovel with a flat edge. It carefully remove thin layers of soil), and a trowel ( used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil).                    It takes years to accomplish your goal. Item_Response: Archeologists have very important jobs. They help find the history of many people all over the world. There have been many important discoveries of important artifacts like finding Fort James and finding George Washington's childhood home. They also have many tools to dig up the past. There are many things to do if you are an archeologist.       One job the archeologists do is rediscovering old forts from the Revolutionary War like James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. The Rediscovery Archaeological Project was ordered to find and rediscover the old James Fort. The fort was built in 1607 by English settlers. The archeologists found pieces of armor and weapons and the floor of the fort. They used computer mapping to find the exact location of the building.They made many maps of the fort.       Another job that many archeologists do is finding the homes or birthplaces of famous historians from all over the world. Many archeologists were interested in finding out more about George Washington's childhood. So they found the home that George Washington's father, Augustine Washington, moved his family to when George was six years old. The location of the house is now known as Ferry Farm. Since the house was actually gone, many archeologists believed that the base of the house was still there. So they started digging in 2003, and found the house in 2004, a year later. They found the kitchen, slave quarters, and the storage houses first. A few years later, they then found the main farmhouse.They had little proof that this really was the Washington household. They carefully used 3D computers to map the house out before the archeologists actually started digging.They also recorded what they found with the computer in the computer. They dug lightly and carefully and found the evidence they needed.       There are many tools that archeologists used to carefully dig up and move important artifacts. There are picks and shovels, which are used to dig into the Earth that is close to the artifact. A whisk and dustpan are used to dust dirt off of artifacts and pick up the dirt. A knife can be used to carefully dig and scrape dirt off of an artifact. A wheelbarrow is used to move artifacts or dirt to different places. A skim shovel is used to carefully remove thin layers of soil from the item. A trowel is probably the most common tool in archeology. It is used to scrape and cut soil to see the different layers.       In conclusion, archeologists do have difficult jobs, but they are important to world history. They help uncover important discoveries all over the world. I want to thank them for all of the history they reveal.

Item_Response: A Day In The Shoes Of An Archeologist                                 The job of an archeologist is very important to our community when it comes to history. They try to help us understand history more and more.They uncover history as if it were hapenning out our front door. With the amazing discoveries they have made and more great ones to come they don't have an easy job. They have to get all the research about something, predict if needed, and start digging. But, I know that it is worth it.        The whole team of archeologists are working all the time. Scientists in labs are looking at and identifying the artifacts while others are finding them. Both procceses take a lot of time but with the help they need they can make something amazing.When it comes to history they have to be working as ghard as they can and giving their work one hundred percent. they know what they are working for.       Being an archeologist takes a lot of hard work and determination. They also use a lot of tools in their work such as a whisk, dustpan, pick, shovel, trowel, knife, skim shovel, and a wheel barrow. A whisk and dustpan are used to brush dirt off and clear away dirt from the excavation site and arifacts. A pick and shovel of course dig to get to the artifacts while a trowel scrapes and cuts to view different types of soil. A skim shovel has a flat edge that is used to carefully remove thin layers of soil with each scoop. Also, a knife is used to scrape dirt away from around the artifacts. Finally, a wheelbarrow is used to carry dirt away from the excavation site or carefully carry artifacts.       Lots of archeologists around the world are looking for answers to mysteries that have come. They might just want to get a little more information about something but, either way they are helping us discover and uncover these mysteries. Some of these include finding the place where George Washington grew up or unlocking the mystery of finding where the mysterious Fort James was or where it went. With all the work the have done we need to thank them for them letting us get a look at the past.

Item_Response: Archeologists At Work           ???Archeologists need to be carful and strong at their job because they have to dig up things. How do the archelogists find all these things? The process of digging on farms are carful ones. Each year many teams will work on them.       There can be up to 35 people on a team! The first team maps the area  using a 3D computer that can track underground. The information is recorded so that people will know what it looked like before people started digging.       Another team focuses on the actual digging, and the place the team does the digging is called a dig.Those archeologists start their dig with what are called skim shovels. These shovels are so small, flat and sharp they can remove thin layers of soil, one at a time. That soil is then placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. This lets dirt fall out while artifacts stay in.       The diggers also use a process called troweling. Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes and wooden picks to remove dirt. It can to two weeks a dig a 25 square foot section! Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects found. The whole process is tresome, but it's worth it.

Item_Response: Arceologists   By Mason Chipman   Part 1    The Dicovery of Jamestown        In 1994, a group people tried finding Jamestown. the main idea was to find some of the secrets and artifacts of Jamestown.        The fort was built in 1607 when settlers from England came to start a new life. At first they thought that the fort was built near the water, so it was easier to dock ships. Later they found out that Jamestown was further away from water for protection from enemy ships.        In 1861 the first objects were discovered. The people were called, arceologists. They found armer, weapons, and valuable things. 100 years later they found the exact spot where the fort was.        The National Park Service led a five- year study on the area to figure out what the land was used for. The people studying used computer software to look at the images there.        That's when they found Jamestown!!! The things they found first were markings on the ground. The markings showed where the walls used to be. The arceologists discovered that Jamestown was in the shape of a triangle. They discovered that it stretched all the way to the river. They  realized that there were stone ledges to hold canons. The arceologists found eleven cellars, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings in where Jamestown stood.        Today , the group finds about 1 million things a year. Such as pottery, tools, coins, and metal toys that kids used to play with. In the 1600s, people in Jamestown also through their garbage  down wells that they didn't use. The arceologists found some of their garbage, it was mostly bones from animals they ate. The information helps use understand how people lived back then. We now know how the settlers beat the indians that often attacked Jamestown. We also know how they survived those many years many years without that much food.        It must have been a big acomplishment finding Jamestown. Maybe someday you can be arceologist.   Part 2   The Discovery of Ferry Farm and George Washington        We all know that George Washington was a soldier and was the first president of the United States of  America or (U.S.A.). But something we do not know is his child hood.         We do know that he lived at Ferry Farm. The only thing is that there were four houses. They know there was a fire at his house. They also know that he smoked clay pipes which they found part of a clay pipe, so they have more proof that this is the right house. Now they know more about Washington's child hood.          Now you can be active by going to Ferry Farm, because there's many oppertunities for kids such as: workshops both indoor and outdoor activities. The kids can also experiance the life when the colonists lived, they can explore the sites, and become junior arceologists. Kids can also sign up for games, classes, and crafts. There's even a website!!!!! So come on down to Ferry Farm and enjoy the colonial life.

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist would be interesting but this is how they work. An archeologist works by finding objects of  past people and studying the object. They find the artifacts by digging with a trowel,skim shovel, or pick and shovel. Once they dig far enough and they found artifacts they study them by what they are and what they were used for. They also have to find the location by using a map.       Then when they find the location they use a 3-D computer to see whats underground and when they get what is under they record it so the people that dig know what to find. They also work by having a team that works on locating where the digging will happen. Once they know where to dig they use a skim shovel to do most of the digging, a skim shovel is used to remove thin layers of soil.  After they dig all the way down and found an object they use a trowel to carefully scrape or cut most of the dirt off.  Also while digging they need to get all of the dirt out of the way so they use the wheelbarrow, while using the wheelbarrow they don't just use it for dirt but also to take an object back that is to big to carry.         While digging they would have to find clues about if it is the right location and is this really the persons place of memories. When archeologist dig they don't always use a skim shovel,  they don't always use it because once they get  close to the object they would start to use a pick and shovel but sometimes these tools are used for the beginning of most digs.  If you are thinking why they do all of this well here's why  they do it to find out more about the past and about the person so we can understand their life more.       Being an archeologists is hard because if they are looking for an object that is 100 years ago they need to find they exact spot for that object.  An archeologist also has to careful while digging because if they dig to low and somebody didn't know someone may fall in.  Also with  the tools they need to be careful cause the knife would be one that they need to be careful with cause someone may get hurt while digging with it or scraping dirt off with it.  They also need to be careful with the pick because if some dropped it  they may get knocked right out of the head.  An archeologist also has to be careful with all artifacts they find.       They have to be careful with artifacts cause some may be fragile and if they drop the artifact it may get ruined and then they can't study the artifact. So, that is how an archeologist would work.

Item_Response: An Archeologists Job                                                                   By: Kaitlyn LeBlanc                  In archeology there are many things to do.  There are 3 main groups.  Group 1 does the mapping.  Group 2 does the digging.  Group 3 finally does the lab work and research.                     Mapping It Out                   Group 1 as I told you before so you should know that this group maps the site out. The map it out part is done using a 3D computer.  The reason archeologists do this is to show the diggers where to dig.  This to me means saving time for more exploration of the dig.  More exploration means more time to lengthen the part of ground dug in.  If you thought this group was awesome wait till you hear about group 2 the diggers.           The Dig                    The diggers, or group 2 as I like to call them or course by the name do the digging.  Digging requires experience you cant just walk over to a dig site and start digging.  With this experience the dig of a site weather it is of George Washington old farm house.  Or maybe even a dig of Fort James the dig takes 35 weeks give or take a few.  While digging the archeologists dig up a layer of soil or dirt or what ever and put it in a bucket with a 1/2 screen at the bottom.  The screen helps the dirt go out and the artifacts if any stay in.            Lab Work                     Finishing up the proses the 3rd group takes the artifacts and takes them to a lab.  At the lab they figure out what they are a part of and where they came from and sometimes what they were used for.  For example in the dig at Washington's old farm house they found a piece of old pipe.  The pipe suggested that Washington left it behind when he left.                          Reading this story really made me want to be an archeologist when I grow up but still maybe a marine biologist.

Item_Response: FINDING THE JAMESTOWN FORT                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Archaeologists they work hard to make sure we know as much as we can about the history of our country. in 1994 a group went to look for the James town fort. They thought that it was located at the river but then they realized that it was far away from the river to protect it from enemy ships.The first objects to ever be found was in 1861 they found armor, weapons, and the building floors.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                The national park service had a five year study on the area and try to see how the land was used. This would help decide were the fort might be. The group used computer mapping to find an image of the area. The first thing they found were marks were the wall had been. the stories that they had heard led them to believe that the fort had been a triangle.                                                                                                                                                                                                                     they had made maps of the area showing that the fort stretched to the river. There they found that a tone wall was lined down the river, they were meant to hold canons. They also found 11 cellars dozens of burial sites and 10 buildings within the wall. Today they find around 1,000,000,000 items a year, they include tools, coins, mettle toys for children, and pottery.            During the 1600s, people threw there trash down a pit or dried up well. while digging they found one of these pits it had the bones of eaten animals in it. The things we found and are still finding help you learn about how the early settlers lived. We know that the powhatan Indians attacked them. We also now know what the settlers did during the time of starvation.

Item_Response: An archeologist has many jobs, such as digging, examining, and plotting. All these jobs are stated here in this essay:                  First, an archeologist digs for artifacts. He/she uses tools like picks, shovels, whisks, dustpans, knives, wheelbarrows, skim shovels, and trowels to dig for artifacts under the ground very easily, and quickly!                  Next, an archeologist examines ground for the remains of any forts, or ancient houses. This relates to Fort James and George Washington's house. Archeologists looked for remains of these ancient places, found their locations, and then dug!                  Finally, an archeologist might use computers to plot where things are underground. This way, he/she will know what they will dig for, and what is under them. If a giant water pipe that can easily be cracked is under them, they won't dig under them and create a giant water fountain! Instead, they will use the computers to find where something of a high cost is hidden. This way, they have a higher chance of finding a valuable ancient artifact quickly.                  As you can see, these are all the jobs that an archeologist does at work. These jobs are digging for artifacts, examining the ground for remains, and using computers to generate graphs of things under the ground. all these qualities used together, along with patience makes a archeologist successful.

Item_Response: An archaeologist has a somewhat important job, because without them we wouldn't know as much as we do today. Archaeologist have to try not to break an artifact or we can't learn much from it. Being an archeologist is hard work because you need to know where to look for an artifact. Most archeologist use high tech equipment like 3D maps that can track what is underground.       Back when we didn't have all the high tech we do today archaeologist had to dig in many different places until they found something to dig up. Since there wasn't backhoes back then all they had to dig with was shovels. They usually go to somewhere that had a flood a long time ago. Archeologist hope that there is something that is interesting about the worlds past.       Archaeologist usually have a team in which help (him/her) to dig more in a shorter time. Most of the biographies    don't have very much on his childhood. Well, that is all about to change. As years go past, archeologists are finding more and more artifacts about Washington's childhood.       People have lived on land known  Ferry Farm for more than 12,000 years. This location makes a perfect place to build a home. So, it is not suprising that     Augustine Washington, Washington´s farther moved there. Since at least four other houses  have been built on the Ferry Farm, archeologist have to find proof that Washington and his family were living there at a time.           Records show that the Washingtons had a fire in their house. To prove that,    Archeologist found piecies of burnt pottery. The diggers also found piecies to clay pipes. We know that Washington smoked clay pipes, so that gives more proof that it is the right house.           The discovery of Washington´s home is very improtant to many reasons. First, it gives the citizens of the United States a better understanding of who                  George Washington was before he became our first president. We also begin to know why he made the decsions he did. Another thing is it histortians learn about the type of life Colonial Americans lived. Alll of these things are the key parts of our past of Americans.

Item_Response: Being an Archeologists is alot of hard work.  You have to find out where the right place is where you have to dig.  Then, you map out the are to make sure it is the right place.  After that, you have to start digging until you find artifacts.  When you found some artifacts you have to dig around them careefully to make sure the atifact doesn't break.  Then, you carefully take it out and take a whisk and start to brush dirt off the artifact carefully.            When you are done with that you give the artifact to another archeologist and they will take it somewhere.  After you find another artifact you take a knife to carefully dig around the artifact to get it out.  When you get it out you take a whisk and clean it.  Once you are done with that you have to take all the artifacts and make sure all the dirt is off it.  Then you take all off them to a plce where people put them in a museum.  An archeologists job is alot of hard work, but it is worth it.

Item_Response: Digging Up the Past                        Have you ever wanted to find a piece of work from years ago? An archeologist is a person who finds artifacts about things like life back in the day.Archeologists also finds bones from what is now dinosaurs they brush them off carefully then bring it to a museum for people to see.                First, we need to see what they do and what the teams are? The archeologist comes in teams of 35 people and the teams try to figure out where the bones are.Some tools they use is the pick and the shovel, the whisk and dust pan, the knife,and etc.The pick and the shovel are used for digging up the earth to get close to the artifact the whisk and the dust pan is used to brush the dirt off of the artifact and finally the knife is used to scrape the dirt off of the artifact.                Secondly, One team of archeologist get the artifacts by a 3-D computer and it tells them what is under the ground then it is recorded so they know where it is! The other team does the digging and they are called the dig team. A fact is that the team that digs, it can take up to a week to dig a 25-square foot section!                 Thirdly, after the digging team digs the dirt the other team study's the dirt this process is long and tiring but it is worth the try because if they do not study it they can miss something that is very important and mess  up the whole process by just doing that.                 In conclusion,you can see how the archeologists find, study and how important this is so we can bring back history in another way.The job of an archeologist is hard and tiring but it is always worth a try they can always use another hand!
